title: turkey marinate
directions: Blend
ingredients by hand;
pour over turkey breast in covered
container.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake turkey
breast
according to directions; marinate during cooking. Good with chicken, also!

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; stir in potatoes, onion, salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture is thickened and potatoes are done.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat whites until foamy (5 minutes).
Add vanilla, cream of tartar and salt.
Increase to medium speed while adding 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, 5 minutes.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Add 1/3 dry ingredients, fold in, add remaining 2/3 dry ingredients in the same way.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and cool.
Chop up vegetables.
Toss with pasta. Add can of crab meat and shrimp (thawed).
Mix together with Ranch salad dressing.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, stir well.
Top with marinade.

title: italian sausage
directions: In electric frypan, cover bottom of pan with olive oil.
Brown sausage links on all sides until brown.
Add green peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Cover.
Let simmer until vegetables are tender. Add seasonings to desired taste.
Cook until sausage is done and vegetables are very tender.

title: 7-up dream salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows.
Stir over low heat until marshmallows melt.
Add lime gelatin to hot mixture.
Beat cream cheese well and add to gelatin mixture.
Whip thoroughly.
Add pineapple and chopped walnuts.
Chill until partially congealed. Combine mayonnaise with whipped cream and fold into gelatin. Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Cool Whip may be substituted for whipped cream.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir all together and bake in greased 8 x 10-inch glass dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lo-cal sandwich
directions: Toast bread.
Add pineapple, lettuce, bananas, cheese and mayo.
A great lunch and no guilt.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more or until onions are golden brown.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In saucepan, heat milk until bubbles form around edge of pan; remove from heat.
Add sugar, salt and 1/4 cup butter; stir until butter melts and cool to lukewarm.
If possible, check temperature of water with thermometer.
Sprinkle yeast over water in large bowl.
Stir to dissolve yeast; stir in the lukewarm milk mixture. Add 4 cups whole wheat flour; beat vigorously with wooden spoon until smooth.
Gradually add rest of whole wheat flour; mix in last of it with hand until dough is stiff enough to leave side of bowl.
Turn dough out on lightly floured pastry cloth.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic, 5 minutes.
Place in lightly greased large bowl; turn dough to bring up greased side.

title: date nut cake
directions: Preheat oven at 300°.
Mix dates and nuts in separate bowl with flour, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: nutty blue cheese rolls
directions: For filling, stir together walnuts, Blue cheese, 1 tablespoon parsley and pepper.
On a lightly floured surface, unfold pie crust.
Spread filling evenly over the crust.
Cut the pastry into 12 wedges.
Starting at wide ends, loosely roll up wedges.
Place rolls, tip side down, on a greased baking sheet.
Just before baking, brush with milk.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and additional parsley.
Bake in a 425° oven about 15 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet with butter flavor Crisco.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed, just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on cooling rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oil in large skillet.
Stir in rice, water chestnuts, mushrooms and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in beaten eggs; cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla (or rum) and walnuts in top of a double boiler and cook until thick.
Cool slightly and add vanilla (or rum) and walnuts.
Pour into cooled baked pie shells. This is a very generous pie filling.
Can also be poured into custard cups.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add remaining ingredients in given order.
Pour into favorite prepared 8-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls onto cookie sheet and scrunch edges together.
Cook according to package directions and allow to cool. Combine mayonnaise, cream cheese and onions.
Mix well and spread onto cooled crust.
Mix broccoli, cauliflower and carrots together; spread on top.
Pat firmly onto cheese mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and olives.
Chill well (at least 2 hours). Cut into pizza slices.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sugar and mayonnaise together.
Combine rest of the ingredients.
Pour mayonnaise mixture on top and mix well.

title: lemonade punch
directions: Mix in a gallon container.
Add enough water to make a gallon. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Add 1-quart ginger ale just before serving.

title: crunch bars
directions: Grease a square pan.
Mix and heat butter, honey, sugar and cinnamon.
Boil about 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla and noodles.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased dish.

title: shoo-fly cake(from true pennsylvania dutch...)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and margarine (cut with pastry blender or two knives), forming crumbly mixture. Reserve 1 1/2 cups on the side.
Mix molasses, boiling water and baking soda (mixture will foam).
Now mix the flour mixture and molasses liquid mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture gently on top so that it does not sink.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes. Check with a toothpick.
Wonderful served slightly warm.

title: spicy chicken and pasta
directions: Cook vermicelli in a covered pot in salted boiling water for 9 minutes only, then drain.
While vermicelli is cooling, mix margarine, soup and cheese, then add Ro-Tel, onion, Worcestershire sauce and chicken.
Check for salt and pepper.
Finally, add the cooked, hot vermicelli and gently mix to blend well.
Check again for salt, then pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hearty potato sauerkraut soup
directions: May add 1 teaspoon Wyler's low-sodium chicken granules, dissolved in 1 cup hot water per cup of chicken broth.

title: spinach rollslincoln, nebraska
directions: Spread on flour tortillas and roll up.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice (into coins) and serve.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10x1 1/2-inch pie plate. Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning. Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chiles.
Mix milk, baking mix, and eggs until smooth in a blender. 15 seconds on high or 1 minute with hand beater.

title: cold veggie salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables; toss lightly. Refrigerate several hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast. Mix until moistened. Cover bowl and place in refrigerator until ready to use. When ready to use roll on floured board to 1/2 or 3/4 -inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake in 400° oven 10 to 12 minutes. (Dough will keep several days.)

title: different asparagus
directions: Drain asparagus.
Arrange on serving platter.
Mix remaining ingredients in small pan and heat to boiling point.
Pour over asparagus.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix oleo, vegetable oil, cocoa and water in a saucepan until blended and let it come to a boil.
Have ready the flour, sugar, buttermilk, baking soda, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix together with mixer.
Pour hot chocolate into mix slowly.
Mix well. Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar, oil and vanilla until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in the zucchini.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in the walnuts.
Add to the first mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: simple souper rice
directions: Prepare soup according to directions on can; then fill can with Minute rice and add to soup when boiling.
Stir.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
"That's it."
Minute rice absorbs soups flavor.
Makes 6 servings.
Especially good with chicken.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix Minute rice and 2 cans of soup.
Spread in bottom of roaster.
Place chicken pieces fat side up on top of rice.
Mix onion soup mix and 1 soup can of water; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together and shape into 4 rolls.
Place on cookie sheet and cover.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add powdered sugar and continue to beat until fluffy.
Combine cornstarch and flour.
Add to butter, along with extract.
Beat well.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
These are light and delicious.

title: deviled dip
directions: Boil eggs.
Separate yolks from whites in 2 different bowls. Add to yolks; mustard, pickle juice, salt, pepper and Miracle Whip. Mix. Makes a delicious dip for crackers or chips.

title: chicken divan(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Arrange cooked, drained broccoli in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Place chicken on top evenly.
Combine undiluted soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
May be refrigerated, covered with plastic, up to 2 days.
Can be multiplied for parties.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and other ingredients.
Stir in all-bran last.
Store in covered container in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Cook in greased muffin tins as needed.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: oven brisket
directions: Place brisket in foil fat side down.
Cover with Woody's cooking sauce.
Seal in foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake for 6 to 8 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage 10 minutes with small amount of water; drain. Layer in buttered casserole, cabbage, soup and cheese, ending with cabbage.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: one bowl refrigeration rolls
directions: Break egg into well-greased bowl.
Melt shortening in boiling water; allow to cool slightly.
Measure into sifter, flour and scant 1/3 cup sugar.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Beat egg in bowl and add melted shortening and dissolved yeast.
Add sifted ingredients. Stir only until mixed.
Dough will be moist and soft.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Roll out 1/2-inch thickness on floured surface; use flour dipped cutter, cut to form rolls.
Brush melted butter on roll, fold in half and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes depending on size.
Dough may be made night before and left in refrigerator overnight.
(Be sure to cover before placing in refrigerator.)

title: broccoli pie
directions: Saute garlic, onion and butter 4 to 5 minutes.
Place with broccoli in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine milk, eggs, flour, salt and pepper in bowl.
Mix well and pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese and stir gently.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: popovers
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, flour and salt for about 1 1/2 minutes.
Add oil.
Beat for 1 more minute (do not overbeat).

title: pie crust cookies
directions: Bake in 325° oven on a greased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lasagne(serves 9 to 12)
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage with spices until done.
Mix tomatoes and tomato paste together.
Add to meat mixture.
Simmer. Mix together eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Boil lasagne noodles.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture and 1/2 meat mixture; layer again, remainder of noodles, cheese mixture and meat mixture.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for cake together 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 round cake pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, margarine and syrup with a wire whisk or hand beater.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake until set, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Serve warm or refrigerate.
Store in fridge.

title: cinnamon raisin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix margarine, salt, 1/2 cup sugar, 4 cups hot water and 4 cups Higluten flour.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix the yeast, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 cup warm water.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water over raisins and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add mixture in small bowl to mixture in large bowl.
Add cooled raisins.
Add 8 to 9 cups Higluten flour, stirring until stiff dough forms.

title: sweet 'n sour ham and pineapple bites
directions: Measure pineapple syrup.
Add water, if necessary, to equal 2/3 cup.
In small saucepan, combine pineapple liquid, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and orange juice.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple chunks, ham and sausage.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in green pepper.
Immediately place in chafing dish or fondue pot. Garnish with fruit.
Serve with decorative toothpicks.
Yields 5 cups.

title: cheese and spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in buttered casserole dish.
Stir well.
Top with sliced cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until brown and bubbly, about 1 hour.

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in slightly salted water until tender; drain. Combine sugar, starch, salt and ginger in saucepan.
Add orange juice.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Stir in margarine, pour over hot carrots, stirring lightly to coat.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In large
bowl with mixer, combine cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and
milk.
Beat gently.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in pie shell.	Freeze	4
to
6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken chow lein
directions: Mix first (8) eight ingredients together in large casserole baking dish.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 can chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; let set overnight.
Split rolls and smear both sides with mix.
Add ham and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon angel food cake
directions: Cook pie filling.
Cover bottom of round bowl with mixture. Cover with layer of pieces of angel food cake.
Continue to alternate layers until bowl is full.
Let stand overnight; chill thoroughly.
Dump onto plate and cover with whipped cream and coconut.

title: bubble bread
directions: Melt margarine and add garlic.
Partially thaw bread and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Dip bread cubes in margarine and garlic mixture.
Roll in cheese.
Place in oven-safe bowl or loaf pan. Let rise to double size.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: three bean baked beans
directions: Brown
hamburger and bacon together with chopped onion. Add catsup.
Mix
all
ingredients together and put in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven (or other stock pot), heat margarine over medium-high heat until bubbly and hot; add onion, celery and carrot and saute until onion is softened, 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over vegetables and stir quickly to combine.
Continuing to stir, gradually add milk; add broth and stirring, bring just to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and let simmer, stirring frequently, for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts (5 to 10 minutes).
Do not boil. Makes about 8 to 10 servings, 1 cup each.
This is a wonderful hearty soup to serve with cornbread or corn muffins.

title: diabetic muffins
directions: Sift together all the flours, blend well; mix all dry ingredients with flours.
Then add the egg, slowly stirring in the milk, plus the butter for a stiff batter.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy; beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth.
Stir in sour cream. Stir in flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Fold in berries.
Spread half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix brown sugar
and cinnamon together and sprinkle mixture evenly over top of the batter.
Spread remaining batter over top of sugar and cinnamon. Bake in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool in pan.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press out cookie dough on a pizza pan.
Bake until done (light brown or dark whichever you prefer).
Let cool completely.
Cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Spread on top of cool cookie crust.
Top with strawberry glaze.
Top with fruit.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add flour and egg yolks.
Beat smooth. Add milk, lemon juice and rind.
Fold in stiffly-beaten egg whites and pour into partially baked crust.
Put in hot oven (425°) and bake until filling is firm to the touch.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and cook in large skillet (greased) at 350° until brown.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Top with the soup.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: In blender, chop quartered seeded oranges.
Pick over cranberries and wash.
Place oranges, cranberries, sugar and nuts (if desired) in a 3-quart casserole.
Stir and mix well. Cover. Microwave 15 to 20 minutes or until cranberries are soft. Stir every 5 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain liquid from pears and heat in a boiler.
Stir in Jell-O until melted.
Add chopped up cream cheese.
Remove mixture from stove and cool.
Mash pears.
Add to mixture.
Add Cool Whip to mixture and stir.
Pour mixture into a bowl and refrigerate until firm.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, salt, parsley, garlic salt, black pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Gently mix thoroughly and shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet and brown meatballs.
Remove from skillet; drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly until jelly is melted, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs and stir well until coated.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish.
Makes 5 dozen.
May use cocktail wieners or hot dogs in place of meatballs.
Serve with crackers.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Cook, drain and crumble bacon.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon bacon grease.
Add onion and saute.
Blend in cornstarch and mustard.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir and reserve liquid into skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Stir in sugar and vinegar.
Add beans, heat and serve, sprinkling with bacon and egg.

title: marinating steak sauce
directions: Mix together.
Let stand over steaks 2 hours before grilling.

title: banana split pudding
directions: In saucepan, cook pudding, milk and water (or cook in microwave); watch very closely.
Stir often and use medium heat on stove.
When thickened, remove from heat.
Cool; when almost cooled, add vanilla.
Cool completely.
Add yogurt and whipped topping, folding in peeled banana.
Put into individual dessert dishes or glass bowl.
Before serving, top with preserves.
Dollop Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate or chocolate sprinkles.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Split wieners lengthwise almost all the way through.
Cut cheese in strips 1/4-inch thick.
Place inside wieners.
Starting at the short corner of roll, roll each around a wiener.
Place on cookie sheet and broil until cheese is bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in pieces for serving.
Put in a casserole and sprinkle with salt, pepper and melted butter.
Add boiling water until one inch deep.
Cover.
Bake at 375° until tender (1 hour or more).
Pour over the chicken 1 cup chicken gravy or undiluted canned mushroom or chicken soup.
Cook 10 minutes.
Season to taste.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Put meat in a large pot.
Cover meat with water to half full. Add tomatoes; mash.
Add salt, pepper, bell pepper, onion, bay leaf and garlic.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes or until meat is almost tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and corn.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Take out bay leaf and discard.
Serve with corn bread.

title: rhubarb syrup
directions: Cut rhubarb.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Strain and save juice.
Combine juice, water and pectin.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add 1 (3 ounce) package raspberry jello.
Stir well to dissolve.
Pour into hot jars to seal.
Makes 3 pints. Good for pancakes and topping on ice cream.

title: cocktail rye pizza snacks
directions: Remove casing from Italian sausage; crumble sausage into large skillet.
Add pork sausage and ground beef.
Add the onion and green pepper.
Cook thoroughly, stirring constantly, until meat is browned.
Drain well on paper towels; also wipe the skillet.
Then return meat mixture to skillet.
Add seasonings and mix well. Heat through until hot, then stir in cheese until melted.
Remove from heat.

title: applesauce lemon salad
directions: Cook applesauce until thick; dissolve candies in hot water and add jello.
Stir to dissolve candies and then add applesauce. Chill.

title: vegetarian baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crunchy green pea salad
directions: Rinse frozen peas in hot water (steam if you use fresh peas). Combine vegetables and nuts with sour cream and dressing.
Toss gently and add pimiento.
Chill and serve.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Place 2/3 cookies in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together margarine and cheese until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip and add dry pudding.
Blend until smooth.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy; add sugar gradually, creaming mixture until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour or spoon into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
in
large
mixing
bowl, except 1 tablespoon of
vegetable
oil.
Heat
the tablespoon of oil in large iron	skillet until very hot.
Pour batter into skillet. Bake in 350°
oven	about
50 minutes or until done and golden brown.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies in a large bowl.
Combine ice cream and Cool Whip and add to cookies.
Mix well.
Spread into rectangular pan and freeze until firm.
Cut into serving size squares.
Store in freezer.
Serves 8.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place graham crackers (broken in halves) on cookie sheet. Sprinkle pecans over crackers.
Melt margarine and butter; stir in sugar until dissolved.
Pour over crackers. Bake 10 to 12 minutes (no longer) at 350°.
Remove from cookie sheet while still very warm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients by hand until smooth.
Add apples, raisins, soda, vanilla, pecans, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes in a long pan (12 x 9-inch).

title: christmas delight
directions: Prepare pudding. Set in refrigerator. Cut cake in bite size pieces.
Drizzle Kirsch over cake pieces.
In a clear bowl with straight sides layer x 3:
1/3 cake, 1/3 pudding mix and 1/3 cherries. Top with toasted almonds.

title: mom's noodles
directions: Beat egg; stir in oil and milk.
Add dry ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll out on floured board and dry well.
Noodles can then be cut and shaken loose.

title: breaded carrots
directions: Place carrots in water in pressure cooker.
Add salt and cook 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool cooker at once.
Melt butter in frypan and brown.
Add bread crumbs; cook until crumbs are brown.
Add lemon juice.
Pour over drained carrots and sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken diable
directions: In a small pan, combine butter or margarine, honey and mustard.
Remove chicken skin.
Heat remaining ingredients.
Place chicken on a shallow pan and pour sauce over.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting frequently (uncovered).

title: dill ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with bread and veggies.

title: joe's low-fat baked catfish
directions: Rinse catfish with water and pat dry.
Next, prepare ingredients; lightly salt and pepper catfish to taste.
Next, take minced garlic and spread over top of catfish fillet (1/2 teaspoon to each or more desirable to taste).
Cut lemon and sprinkle juice over catfish.
Spray baking dish with no stick spray.
Place in preheated oven at 350°.
Bake approximately 1/2 hour or until catfish is light golden brown on top.

title: mexican cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla
and
nuts.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chandra's ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in an ice cream freezer and finish filling with milk.
Freeze and enjoy.
This ice cream is more like a sherbet.

title: fred's chocolate chip wheat germ pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Let cool.
Add sugar.
Mix.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crescent caramel swirl
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Coat bottom and sides of a 12-cup Bundt pan with 2 tablespoons of the melted butter; sprinkle pan with 3 tablespoons of the nuts.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining melted butter. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: pizza bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir sausage, onion, green pepper and seasoning until brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in sauce, olives, mushrooms and 2 tablespoons Bisquick.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
After cooking for one minute, pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with pepperoni.

title: red, white and blue jello mold
directions: In four separate bowls, dissolve each package of gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to each and stir. Pour one bowl of blue gelatin into an oiled or sprayed fluted tube pan.
Chill until almost set, about 30 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Hand chop carrots and celery, use scissors for green onion tops.
Set oven to 325.
Put casserole pan with heavy cover in oven to heat.
A heavy casserole with a tight fitting cover works best.
Meanwhile, in a sauce pan, melt margarine and add rice.
In another pan heat the consomm and water, just before it starts to boil, pour rice and margarine into consomm.
Take hot casserole out of oven and pour rice mixture into it.
Return to oven and bake 35 minutes.
Serves 10 - 12.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla and peanut butter and cream until smooth.
Add flour.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave manicotti
directions: Prepare manicotti conventionally as package directs and drain.
combine ricotta cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Fill each manicotti shell with about 1/3 cup cheese mixture.
(Can split shells to make this easier.)
Arrange shells in 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
In medium pan, cook mushrooms covered on high for 2 - 3 minutes until tender-crisp.
Drain and discard liquid.
Stir mushrooms into spaghetti sauce.
Spoon sauce over shells.
Shield 2 long sides of baking dish with 2 inch wide strips of smooth foil.
(I don't do this).
Cook covered on high 8 minutes; discard foil and rotate dish.
Cook covered 4 - 6 minutes more until hot and bubbling.
Let stand covered for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: confetti tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except egg slices in a medium bowl and stir to blend.
Spoon into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes or until bubbly and heated through. Garnish with egg slices.

title: potato scallop
directions: Combine potatoes and onion in casserole.
Mix soup with enough milk to make it suitable for blending.
Pour over the potatoes and onion.
Cover top of mixture completely with thin slices of American cheese.
Sprinkle liberally with grated Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Use salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in oven at 350° to 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice and water in baking dish.
Place chicken on rice. Pour soups over chicken.
Do not dilute.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/4 ketchup, egg, crumbs and onion pad.
Put beef over mixture and mix well.
Pat the beef mixture on wax paper into a 10 x 6 pan.
Spread remaining ketchup over meat within 1/2 inch of the long sides and 1 1/2 on the small sides.
Top with mustard and relish.
Place 4 slices of cheese on top then set remaining cheese aside.
Roll up loaf jellyroll style on wax paper.
Then seal seems and ends well.
Place loaf, seam side down, in a greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes.
Return loaf if cheese is not melted on top for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chicken-waldorf salad
directions: Cook and debone chicken breasts.
Dice chicken and apples. Add bananas and drained pineapple chunks.
Add nuts.
Mix well with desired amount of lite Miracle Whip.
Serve on lettuce bed.

title: ammy's little cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Use an electric mixer and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Then beat in extracts.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine dry mixture and creamed one.
Make round balls about 2 inches across.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: huckleberry pie or other berries
directions: In double boiler melt milk and marshmallows over hot water; cool.
Stir in Cool Whip. Stir in berries.
Pour in pie shell. Put in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry-banana punch
directions: Place fruits and juice in blender and liquefy.
Add water. Serves 10 to 12.

title: rice and sour cream casserole(arroz con jocoqui)
directions: May be made with macaroni and noodles or whole hominy instead of rice.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Add bouillon cubes to water and simmer 20 minutes.
Add frozen broccoli and cook 30 minutes.
Add chicken soup and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Keep fire very low so soup will not scorch on bottom.

title: john's dill potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in a buttered baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, then add remaining.
Beat 2 eggs and 1 cup whipping cream; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve strawberry Jell-O in boiling water. Add thawed strawberries, pineapple and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into an 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch container. Refrigerate until set.
Spread softened sour cream over set mixture.
Pour on remaining mixture.
Let set, then enjoy!
(If not using sour cream, pour in pan all mixture and set.)

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Combine corn, sour cream, eggs and oil in a bowl.
Beat well. Stir in corn meal with baking powder.
Pour in a buttered (greased) 10-inch skillet and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: italian rice pie
directions: In a large bowl, pour all ingredients, but rice and raisins. Beat well.
Add cooled rice.
Pour in pie dish and sprinkle raisins on top.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk with mixer.
Let set for a few minutes to set up, then fold in Cool Whip and sour cream by hand.
Layer bananas and vanilla wafers, then pudding mixture.
Keep layering until pudding is used up.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook butter, flour and milk until thick, stirring constantly. Add chicken broth, half and half and garlic powder.
Add broccoli. Cover and cook over medium heat until hot.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 1 hour.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Cook the beef according to the package directions on the taco seasoning package.
Add the cream cheese to this mixture during the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Let cool.
Cook the pasta according to the directions on the box.

Drain, then toss with the margarine. Fill the shells with the meat mixture and place in a casserole dish. Top with the taco sauce, crushed chips and cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. After cooking, top with the sour cream, lettuce, scallions and tomatoes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Swirl in blender for smoother dip, if desired.
Serve with raw vegetables or wheat crackers.

title: whiskey macks
directions: Line a large baking sheet with foil.
Put cocoa, corn syrup and whiskey in a medium-size saucepan; stir over low heat until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir gingersnaps and walnuts into whiskey mixture; allow to cool slightly.
Roll pieces of mixture into balls about the size of a walnut, then flatten into even rounds.
Place on baking sheet.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until firm.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add water and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O.
Cool and add 4 cups of fresh sliced peaches.
Pour into 2 baked and cooled pie shells.

title: cinnamon popovers
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; blend just until smooth.
Place well-greased muffin pans in a 425° oven 3 minutes or until a drop of water sizzles when dropped in them.
Remove pans from oven; fill each muffin cup half full with batter.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 12 to 15 minutes or until popovers are firm. Serve immediately.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: chicken gumbo and rice
directions: Cut up the chicken and season with salt and pepper.
Heat fat in soup kettle.
Add chicken and ham; cover tightly and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper, parsley, tomatoes and okra.
Now, add boiling water and let simmer for 2 hours.
Serve in a tureen.
Accompany with a bowl of rice.
Or serve in soup bowls with a mound of rice.
Crabs, oysters or shrimp may be substituted for the chicken.

title: venison roast (deer)
directions: Select boneless roast (4 to 6 pounds).
Slit sides and top at 3-inch intervals and stuff with pieces of chopped onion, bay leaf, salt, pepper, ground cloves and allspice.
Pour vinegar to cover meat.
Leave in a covered dish for 12 hours or more.
To cook, lift out meat, coat with lard and flour and brown on both sides quickly.
Pour on the same vinegar, cover and cook for 20 minutes to the pound.
Slice and serve hot or cold.

title: pam's english toffee
directions: Cook butter and sugar over medium-high heat until color of brown paper bag, about 7 minutes (never remove from heat when yellow).
Stir in almonds.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread melted Hershey bars on top.
Sprinkle walnuts over top.
Cool and break into chunks.

title: peachy bran muffins
directions: Combine yogurt and cereal; mix lightly.
Add raisins, carrot, sugar, oil and egg whites; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to cereal mixture; stir just until moistened.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin cups, filling each almost full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.
Prep time:
15 minutes.
Bake time:
18 to 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Stir all ingredients and pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.

title: pammy's famous zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.
Put into 2 greased bread pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You'll love it!

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/4 cup cornstarch, flour, salt, 1/4 cup water, egg and 1/4 cup chicken broth; beat until smooth.
Dip pork into batter.
Fry in deep, hot oil until golden.
Drain; set aside.

title: coconut rice krispies cookies(from karen warriner scheiding's 8th grade home ec class)
directions: Into a saucepan, put dates, nuts, salt, water and oleo.
Boil 1 minute; cool.
Add Rice Krispies.
Shape by teaspoonful into ball. Roll into coconut.
Place on wax paper.

title: apple pecan cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine apple pie filling, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in the
nuts.
Spread
the mixture in pie crust and refrigerate remaining mixture.

title: pecan chess pie(1962 cook'n contest winner; nan won this in 1962)
directions: Melt butter or margarine and add blended sugar and meal.
Add eggs, vinegar and vanilla.
Add nuts and raisins (if used) and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 325°.
The top will be a golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream, for 2 minutes, then add sour cream.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to package direction and drain.
Run cold water over it.
Cut up onions, cucumbers and tomatoes in small pieces.
Add Salad Supreme and Catalina dressing.
Mix well. Chill.

title: salmon and shells casserole
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid; set salmon aside.
Add enough water to salmon liquid to make 1 cup.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Add soup and water; mix well.
Stir in shells, salmon, celery and lemon juice.
Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, until shells are tender.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mash
cottage
cheese.	Separate
eggs.
Beat egg yolks and add
to cottage cheese along with sugar, butter, cream and flour. Beat
egg
whites
until
stiff and fold into mixture. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.	Time of preparation: 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crumble crackers and put in a buttered 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over crackers and bake 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate delite cake
directions: Beat together cream cheese and margarine.
Add powdered sugar to mixture.
Dissolve chocolate in hot water and add to mixture. Blend well.
Put half of mixture in batter; reserve half for icing.

title: five hour stew
directions: Put in layers, starting with the meat, into a casserole dish or pan.
Bake 5 hours at 325°, covered.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes; boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese and chips.
Put in baking dish, top with cheese and then the potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, covered.
Remove cover during the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: busy-day cheese rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add shortening, egg and half the flour.
Beat until mixed.
Add remaining flour.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Let rise, covered, in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Divide into 12 portions.
Place in greased muffin cups.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetable goulash
directions: Heat
the
oil
in a casserole;
saute the onions 5 minutes. Add
the
green
peppers;
saute 5 minutes.
Stir in the tomatoes, potatoes, mixed vegetables, salt, pepper, paprika and sugar. Bring to a boil and cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Mix together the
flour
and water; stir into the vegetables until thickened. Serves 8.
Calories:
95 per serving.

title: russian rye dip
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, dill and Durkee spice together.
Rinse dried beef in water.
Drain and add cut up into small pieces.
Add to mixture.
Buy a round loaf of rye bread, hollow out center and fill with dip.
Cut remaining pieces of bread into chunks.
Arrange around bread loaf.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda
and
salt;
set
aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar,
brown
sugar
and
vanilla extract; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking
pan.
Bake
at
for
to 25 minutes. Cool; cut into thirty-five 2-inch squares.

title: apple-pear coffee cake
directions: Combine butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Fold in apple and pear.
Stir in vanilla. Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: jiffy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes open.
Then top with bacon strips.
Cook another 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon pecan pancakes
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Add egg and oil.
Add milk and stir, adding more milk until mixture reaches the consistency of cake batter.
Heat griddle to 325°.
Pour batter (1/2 cup per pancake) onto hot greased griddle.
Turn just as pancake begins to develop bubbles on top.
(Decrease heat if pancake is too brown.) Serve with warm syrup, fruit preserves or whipped cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir thoroughly and spread in a buttered cookie or jelly roll pan.
Cool and cut to desired pieces.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Transfer mixture to a 9 x 13-inch pan or deep casserole dish and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
When done, mash all ingredients together as you would mash potatoes.
If too dry, add a little milk.
Put in greased casserole dish and dot with butter.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in small amount of water until tender. Saute onion in oleo. Mix 1/2 Ritz crumbs, cheese, milk, smashed squash and sauteed onions. Stir to blend. Place in casserole dish (greased). Crumble 1/2 tube Ritz and place on top. Bake at 350° uncovered until slightly browned.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, limeade, condensed milk and food coloring in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with chocolate shaving or slice of fresh lime.

title: alex's chinese eggs
directions: Lightly grease small skillet; add all ingredients and cook until done.
Additional soy sauce may be added.
Serve with buttered toast and juice.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese in the center of each chicken piece.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with wooden picks.

title: e-z chicken
directions: Sprinkle dry mix in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add rice. Cut up chicken and place over rice.
Spoon mushroom soup over chicken and pour water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Drain clams; reserve broth (add enough water to make 2 cups). Melt butter in a large saucepan; saute onions.
Add remaining ingredients and water to cover vegetables.
Bring to a boil; simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add clams; turn off heat, cover and let stand 2 minutes or until clams are hot.
Serve with warm buttered pilar crackers if you wish.

title: chicken-n-wine
directions: Line chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put 1 slice of cheese on each breast.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients; add milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over batter. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: dan's puff pastry and cheese
directions: Thaw pastry sheets for 15 minutes.
Separate sheets.
Slice cheeses in approximately one-inch thick slices horizontally. Alternate cheese slices on thawed pastry sheet (making a long block of cheese), first Monterey Jack and then cream cheese slices.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together flour, margarine, and chopped nuts. Press in 9x 13 pan. Bake at 400 degrees for 8 minutes (watch so it doesn't burn). Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 cool whip. Mix pudding and milk together. Spread over cooled cream cheese mixture. Spread on rest of cool whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: old fashioned mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Pour boiling water over dates and nuts.
Set aside.
Cream mayonnaise and sugar; add melted chocolate (can substitute Hershey's chocolate syrup) and vanilla.
Drain dates and nuts and add to batter alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake in 2 loaf pans 1 hour at 325°.
Test before removing from oven.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except pastry shell; mix well. Pour into prepared shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden. Cool and refrigerate leftovers.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in chili powder.
You can make a log or ball.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, and cocoa.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute (Timing accurately).
Add salt and vanilla.
Blend in peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by tsp. on wax paper. Yield 4 dozen.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients with enough buttermilk to make a thin mixture. Pour into greased skillet.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mushroom gravy hamburgers
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, eggs, soda crackers and seasoned salt thoroughly.
Heat a medium size cast iron skillet with vegetable oil.
Make 1-inch thick hamburgers.
Arrange in skillet and brown slowly on both sides, using lid to cover and meat will stay moist, approximately 20 minutes.
Put mushroom soup on top of each hamburger, large spoonful at a time.
Do not dilute.
Use empty can to measure 2/3 cup water; pour in pan along sides of hamburgers, so doesn't touch tops.
Sprinkle oregano on top of each soup covered hamburger; return lid to skillet.
Reduce heat and simmer 1/2 hour. Juices will blend on their own.

title: centennial squares
directions: Combine graham crackers and oleo and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut over crumb mixture.
Place chocolate chips on top of coconut, then sprinkle on walnuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add the tomato sauce, taco mix and salsa.
In another bowl, combine the cottage cheese, eggs and oregano.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Prepare pudding.
Add sour cream.
Layer:
cake, pudding mixture, then cherry filling.
Make ahead of time and refrigerate.

title: frito pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, stir chili and add water until smooth.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking casserole dish, spread half of chili to bottom of dish.
On top, add Fritos, onion and cheese.
Repeat procedure with a second layer.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry-spinach salad
directions: To prepare fresh spinach, wash leaves thoroughly using cold, running water.
Pat dry on paper towels and trim off tough stems and ribs, as necessary.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Be sure to have 2 cups broth when chicken is done.
Lift out chicken and take off bone.
Put 2 tablespoons chopped onion in broth and boil.
Mix soups and milk in broth on low heat until warm.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish and spread chicken over entire pan.
Pour soup mixture over chicken, then sprinkle dressing on top.
Pour melted butter over dressing and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: a simple teriyaki chicken
directions: Place
chicken	in
a	"pot".	Mix
the
"Coke"
(yes, Coke!!!), soy sauce, ginger
and
green onion and pour it over the chicken.
Cook covered over medium heat.
When it comes to a boil, remove the	lid
and
cook	until
the liquid is gone, stirring occasionally.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until golden brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add thyme.
Cook or steam vegetables in separate pan.
When onions and celery are done, add chicken and stir-fry until golden.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Pour into an ungreased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: double raspberry swirl
directions: Combine thoroughly crumbs, oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar. Press into 9 x 9-inch pan (or 9 x 13-inch pan if doubled).
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl.
Mix together milk, eggs and butter.
Add this mixture to potato mixture.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge of filling comes out clean.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with nonstick spray.
Line the pan with bagels (it should take between 3 to 4 bagels to line 13 x 9-inch pan).
Saute sausage; drain well and sprinkle over bagels. Cover sausage with cheese.
Beat together remaining ingredients. Pour over sausage/cheese bagels.
Sprinkle with cinnamon (optional).
Refrigerate overnight!
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This dish is even better as a leftover.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9x5x3 loaf pans.
Mix flour with baking soda, cream of tartar, and salt.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pecans, lemon rind, and mashed bananas.
Add four mixture, 1/2 c. at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in water and vanilla pour into prepared pans.
Bake 55-60 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center of bread comes out clean.
Remove bread from pan and put on wire cake rack.
Cool completely.

title: mushroom cheeseburger pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan. Unroll dough and place on a greased pan.
Starting at center, press out with hands.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and mushrooms.
Spoon hamburger mixture over partially baked crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers.
Stir well and pour over crackers.
Marinate overnight.
Stir frequently during the day so crackers absorb oil mixture.
Can be frozen for future use. Great at New Year's or any party.

title: velvet chicken
directions: Use this chicken in stir-fry dishes.
Stir-fry vegetables first with shredded ginger, adding velvet chicken last in order to heat only.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Process until ice cubes are crushed.

title: angel food topping cocoa fluff
directions: Beat in chilled bowl all the above ingredients until stiff enough to hold peaks.
Chill.

title: flaky sausage snacks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Unfold pie crusts according to package directions.
Remove both sheets.
Place flattened pie crusts on cutting board.
Cut each pie crust circle into 24 triangles. Place sausage at wide end of triangle; roll up.
Place, point side down, on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
If desired, serve with cocktail sauce.
Makes 48 snacks.

title: honey raisin bran muffins(reduced-fat)
directions: In large bowl, stir together the cereal, flour, sugar and baking soda.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Beat egg whites, honey, prunes, molasses and buttermilk.
Add egg mixture to the flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Add raisins.
Put in airtight container and refrigerate overnight.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown cut up sausages (about 1-inch pieces).
Place 1/2 bread cubes on bottom of dish.
Cover with sausage.
Top with remaining bread.
Sprinkle on top with grated cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Pour over bread and sausage mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: crockery barbecued beef
directions: In large bowl, combine cola, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, garlic, bouillon granules, mustard, chili powder and red pepper. Reserve 1/2 cup for sauce.
Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut into pieces and place meat and onions in crock-pot (at least 3 1/2-quart).
Pour liquid (except the 1/2 cup reserved) over meat. Cover and cook 10 to 12 hours on low heat setting or 5 to 6 hours on high.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Add salt and mix well. Let stand 24 hours, then drain.
In a large kettle, combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumber mixture and bring to a boil again. Spoon pickles into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together with 1 cup of pecans.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Make into ball.
Roll in 1 cup pecans. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: italian parmesan chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing. In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients. Dip chicken in mixture, covering each completely. Place on baking sheet. Pour remaining dry ingredients on top. Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients well in a mixer.
Preheat oven to 325°. Pour batter into a well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch).
Bake at 325° for 60 to 80 minutes.
Test with toothpick in center of loaf. When no dough sticks to toothpick, it is done.

title: mayumi's chicken yakitori
directions: For marinade, combine soy sauce, Mirin, sugar and cornstarch and boil.
When it cools, marinate the meat for 20 minutes. Thread meat and onions alternately on bamboo skewers.
Broil 15 minutes at 375°, turning once and brushing with marinade 2 or 3 times.
Serve hot.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Saute chopped onions in margarine; add flour, stirring until smooth and lightly browned.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in hot sauce, seasonings and seafood.
Cook over low heat until shrimp turn pink.
Stir in parsley.

title: delightful fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple in a pan.
Let mixture come to a boil for 1 minute.
Then add to mixture, cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Stir.
Put into freezing unit for 1 minute.

title: colonel cotten cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla wafers and milk.
Add coconut and nuts.
Spray tube pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mary's fudge
directions: Butter dish and line with nuts.
Mix all except chocolate chips and marshmallow together, bring to a boil and stir constantly. When mixture starts on high boil for exactly 10 minutes, remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Beat well until chips are dissolved.
Then add marshmallow.
Stir and beat until marshmallow disappears and thickens a little.
Pour into buttered dish with nuts.
Makes 5 pounds of candy.

title: anchovy dip
directions: Blend well mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Serve with crisp vegetables (radishes, carrots, cucumber slices, celery, cauliflower, broccoli).

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft; add sugar and cream together.
Add flour and eggs and beat well.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken jambalaya*
directions: Put flour and salt in paper bag.
Place chicken in bag and shake to coat.
Brown chicken lightly in oil and place in large casserole dish with cover.
Brown rice, garlic and onion in pan in which chicken was browned, using additional if necessary.
Add tomatoes, 1 teaspoon salt and other seasonings.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check and add water if dry.
(Makes 6 servings.)
Exchanges:
1 bread, 2 fats and 4 low-fat meats.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix limeade in mixer with milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix until creamy.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate until firm.

title: old-timey chicken pastry
directions: Place hen in a large pot.
Add enough water to cover. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until tender.
Using warm water, mix flour and Crisco to form a biscuit like dough.
Roll out into thin sheet of dough. Allow to set and slightly dry. Cut into strips 2 x 5-inch.
Drop into boiling chicken broth, a few strips at a time. Allow to cook for 15 to 20 minutes without stirring.
Serve with candied yams.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Dump together first 5 ingredients.
Beat well, then add chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken risotto
directions: In large skillet, lightly brown rice in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is done. Top with cheese; allow to melt.

title: christmas bell and tree cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg together good.
Sift together, then stir in the flour, soda and salt.
Make into stick and chill. Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Heat oven to 375° and cook for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: In a mixing bowl beat first four ingredients until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: walnut crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Mix in water and vanilla, then flour and nuts.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll in 1-inch balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 10 minutes. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: zepolies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, Ricotta, eggs and vanilla to make dough.
Heat small pot with Crisco oil.
Drop balls of dough into oil.
When golden brown, remove and drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Butter casserole dish and pour in layers, starting with broccoli and then end with chicken on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Season with salt.
When chicken is tender, take out of broth and remove meat from bones.
Put meat back in the broth. Add potatoes and saffron.
Add squares of pot pie dough and cook 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir well and chill.

title: baked fish chowder
directions: Use fresh or frozen fish (if frozen, put in that way, but stir chowder when partly cooked).
Put all ingredients except cream, in a very large casserole or 2 casseroles, 2 1/2-quart capacity. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Heat cream to scalding before serving and add to chowder.
Makes 8 to 10 servings, 1 bowl each.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Parboil sweet potatoes; cut each lengthwise in quarters.
Arrange in ungreased casserole or oblong baking dish.
In small saucepan stir together sugar, cornstarch and orange peel.
Slowly add orange juice.
Add butter.
Stir constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Pour hot mixture over sweet potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes, covered with foil.
Remove foil and cool slightly before serving.

title: bacon and broccoli salad
directions: Mix together cider vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add sauce to broccoli, bacon, walnuts and raisins.
Mix together and refrigerate at least 5 hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together
flour, soda, cinnamon, sugar, nutmeg and salt. Mix well,
eggs, water, oil, pumpkin, nuts and raisins. Stir well. Pour into 4 greased and floured pound coffee cans. Bake in 350° oven
about 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert and remove from cans.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Make one (9-inch) pie shell.
Put it in the refrigerator while you make the pie filling.
Start heating the oven to 425°.
Beat the egg slightly with a fork to mix the white and yolk.
Stir in the pumpkin and add sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger. Stir in milk.
Pour the filling into the pie shell.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Prepare countertop by wiping off with a clean damp cloth. Sprinkle evenly with flour from a sifter.
Have a tablespoon, table knife or spatula and rolling pin ready for preparing the candy and spreading the peanut butter.

title: rainbow fruit sticks
directions: Cut the tops off the strawberries, put the strawberries on toothpicks.
Do the same with the blueberries, grapes and orange pieces.
Put the sticks on the plate.
Make them look like a rainbow.
(Can use other fruit.)

title: microwaved cauliflower au gratin
directions: Remove outer leaves from cauliflower and trim stem close to base.
Wash and place cauliflower on a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Let stand while making cheese sauce.
Melt butter 1 minute on High.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in milk and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened, stirring every minute.
Add cheese and stir to blend.
Place cauliflower on serving plate and pour sauce over top.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: extra good fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boiling and boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Break candy bars into small pieces into a large bowl.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour hot syrup over this. Stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Stir until cool.
Makes 7 pounds.

title: veggie pizza bites
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Unroll pizza crust dough; press dough on bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 8 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: fettucine spinach bake(serves 6)
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with Pam.
Add in garlic, mushrooms and onions.
Simmer until mushrooms are tender and then add spinach and water.
Cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
Mix together spinach mixture, cooked noodles and cottage cheese.
Place in Pam sprayed 11 x 15-inch baking pan.
Top with shredded cheese and Parmesan. Bake in a 475° oven for 1 hour.

title: dussy ole boy's famous hot chocolate
directions: Heat milk in microwave for 50 seconds.
Add ice cream, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Heat for 1 minute.
Add malt mix and hot chocolate mix and stir well.
If not totally heated, put back in microwave for a few more seconds.
Makes 1 cup.

title: corn mushroom bake
directions: In saucepan, stir flour into creamed corn.
Add cream cheese and onion salt, stir and melt.
Add whole corn, mushrooms and Swiss cheese. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lime jello and pineapple salad
directions: Heat milk and melt in it 16 large marshmallows.
Add Jell-O, softened cream cheese and crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate until partially set, then add Dream Whip (whipped) and mayonnaise.
Put in large cake pan to set.

title: butch's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and beaten eggs.
Warm applesauce and add to mixture.
Add missed dry ingredients.
Last, add nuts and raisins (floured).
Bake at 300°.
Takes a long time to bake; rises very little.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Mix salt in meal, then pour water in the meal.
Add enough water to thin it so it will pour out of the bowl real slow.
Drop batter by spoonfuls on a hot, oiled griddle or skillet.
Turn until both sides are brown.
You will have to re-oil the skillet between each panful.

title: sweet red pepper relish
directions: Note:
Sweet green peppers may be used.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Place crackers in a large plastic bag, pour in oil and toss to coat.
Add dressing and toss again to coat.
Bake at 250° for 15 - 20 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil hen in seasoned water. Cool, debone and cut into bite-sized pieces. Melt butter in large skillet and add drained mushrooms, onions and celery. Saute 10 minutes. Add parsley flakes and chicken. Cover and let sit 10 minutes. Add soup and sour cream. Break spaghetti into bite-sized pieces and cook as directed on package. Combine with chicken. Bake, uncovered, in 300° oven until hot. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: iced tea punch(1 gallon)
directions: *May substitute 9 regular size tea bags.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook cappelini and rinse in cold water.
Combine other ingredients and toss.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: fresh vegetable dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Cover.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Serve with celery sticks and other raw vegetables.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel pears and slice very thin.
Put about 1/4 of pears in a large pan, covering with sugar.
Alternately add pears and sugar, until you've used them all.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook about 2 hours, stirring often.

title: broccoli with walnuts
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Melt 1 stick butter in small saucepan.
Add flour and broth granules.
Cook a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk gradually and stir until smooth and thick.
Pour this sauce over the broccoli.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter in hot water; add stuffing mix and toss thoroughly.
Add walnuts and mix.
Spoon on top of broccoli and bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: cowboy beans - the right way!
directions: Thoroughly wash and pick over beans, (be sure to get out all those little pieces of gravel) then put the beans in a mixing bowl. Drown them real good in cold water and let em' soak overnight (that'll soften em' up some).

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake yellow cake according to directions.
Punch holes in cake while hot.
Warm pineapple with 1 cup sugar until warm and liquid; pour over hot cake.
Cool, then spread pudding that has been fixed by directions on the box.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding. Sprinkle on coconut and chopped nuts (optional).
Refrigerate.

title: hormel chili dip(appetizer)
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Top with chili and cover with shredded cheese.
Put in a 350° oven and bake until cheese is melted.
Serve with Tostado chips or large corn chips.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Layer in crock-pot 3 times:
meat and onion, sauce, mushrooms and pepperoni and then cheese.
Top with cheese.
Cook on low for 5 hours.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt brown sugar and margarine.
Let cool, then mix in vanilla, eggs and flour.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into large cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: best chicken salad in the world
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then add rest.
Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: chicken breasts with ginger marmalade
directions: Melt butter. Stir in the ginger marmalade.
Blend well. Spread on both sides of the chicken breasts.
Roll chicken breasts in the chopped nuts.
Sprinkle on the coconut.
Now, roll up the chicken breasts.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Bake the chicken breasts in a greased roasting pan for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook rice according to directions. Mix broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and soups until well blended.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together, freeze. When ready to serve, partially thaw and pour 4 quarts seven-up over frozen juices to make a slushy punch.

title: baked ham cherry-sherry
directions: Drain juice from cherries into saucepan.
Blend with pulp and juice of oranges and lemon, ginger, brown sugar and sherry.
Simmer until sugar dissolves.
Place ham in baking pan; pour on warm sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in a slow oven (300°) for 25 minutes per pound.
Baste with sauce every 15 to 20 minutes.
About 15 minutes before ham is done, pour brandy over the ham.
At end of cooking period, pour pan juices into saucepan and bring to boiling.
Add cherries; simmer 5 minutes.
Slice ham and serve with sauce.

title: broccoli-cauliflower scallop
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower separately by package directions; do not overcook.
Drain and cool.

title: sue's rolls
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients over low heat and add 1 teaspoon salt.
When stove mixture is cool, add eggs.
Beat them; add yeast.
Pour over flour and mix well.
Set aside until doubled in bulk, 2 or 3 hours.
This mixture will keep in the refrigerator up to a week if mashed down every day.

title: cold oven pound bake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and salt alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake in oven 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remember to start cake in cold oven.

title: french toast
directions: Beat with fork until blended the eggs, salt, sugar, milk and nutmeg or vanilla.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Oil bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the coconut and nuts.
Prepare the cake mix and pour over the coconut and nuts. Cream the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar mixture well. Mixture will be thick.
Glob the mixture on the contents in cake pan.
Batter will raise to top while baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: patty's party roll-ups
directions: Blend all ingredients in any order with hand mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Spread evenly onto 6 burrito size flour tortillas.
Roll each spread tortilla fairly tightly and wrap snugly in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Unwrap and slice into 1/2-inch pinwheels.
Arrange on a serving plate flat. Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: mexican crock-pot dip
directions: Brown sausage and beef in separate pans with onion.
Drain well.
Layer sausage, beef and cheese in crock-pot with tomatoes and juice and peppers.
Cook on high, stirring periodically, until ingredients are hot and bubbly and well blended.
Turn down to low.
Serve with restaurant style tortilla chips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish. Cover with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° until bubbly around edges, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pot dinner
directions: Fry your beef and bacon.
Mix together your canned ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Add beef and bacon (crumbled).
Stir together and simmer until done, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix marinade in large pot, add up to 50 prepared chicken wings.
Simmer, covered, about 25 minutes.
Put into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 1/2 hour at 325°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Combine preserves, buttermilk and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° to make 1 loaf pan.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic, and green chilies in oil until soft. Add tomatoes, chicken broth, and beef bouillon. Mix in spices and simmer for 1 hour. Top with crushed tortillas and cheese.

title: hot hominy
directions: Mix and heat.
Pour into casserole dish and top with grated cheese (Cheddar) and crushed Fritos.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk, parsley and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce. Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more or until potatoes are done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: *Beat egg whites and add at last.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 4 deep cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: better than sex cake
directions: While cake is still slightly warm, poke full of holes with toothpick.
Pour fudge topping over cake.
Cool.
When ready to serve, top with whipped topping and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss all non-dressing ingredients.
Mix dressing ingredients well and combine with the broccoli mixture.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and water until blended smooth.
Add dry ingredients and 1/2 package of strawberries.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla to the eggs, beating well again.
Mix separately, according to package directions, 1 package instant vanilla pudding.
Combine egg and sugar mixture, pudding mixture, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 2 cups cream (or evaporated milk).
Add enough whole milk (approximately 1 1/2 quarts) to fill a 1-gallon ice cream freezer can to the 3/4 full level.
Place can in freezer tub and crank until hardened.
Makes 1 gallon of ice cream.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix melted butter and sugar with mixer until creamy. Add bourbon. Cream in blender until perfectly smooth (this is the secret). Add nuts.
Set in refrigerator until firm enough to roll into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on wax paper or a large pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Using 2 tablespoons, dip balls into chocolate and completely cover.
Place separated balls on large pan. Refrigerate until firm.
They keep better if refrigerated or frozen.

title: party mix
directions: In a saucepan, heat oil, Worcestershire, garlic salt, 1 teaspoon seasoned salt and hot pepper sauce.
In a large roasting pan, combine the cereals, nuts and pretzels.
Stir oil mixture well.
Drizzle over cereal mixture, tossing to coat evenly.

title: baked ziti
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook pasta according to package directions for 8 minutes; drain.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Bake ready-made pie crust according to package instructions. Prepare instant chocolate pudding according to package instructions. Pour pudding into pie crust. Layer Cool Whip on top of pudding. Sprinkle grated chocolate bar on top of Cool Whip. Refrigerate until served.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add all ingredients except oil and flour.
Add these last.
Beat approximately 4 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or longer if needed.

title: pepper steak
directions: Steak:
Cut round steak into 2-inch strips; salt, pepper, flour and brown.
Add chopped green pepper and chopped onion, then soy sauce and beef bouillon with about 2 cups water.
Cover and cook slowly about 1 hour.
Then add enough cornstarch to make gravy.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Stir herbs and seasonings into oil; warm slightly. Pour over crackers and toast lightly in a 350° oven.

title: out of pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until done with only enough water to cover.
Cook onions and celery in butter until tender, adding flour and cooking until smooth.
Add milk to make a light white sauce.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce in with potatoes, simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: glazed carrots and onions
directions: Cook carrots and onions until tender-crisp.
Drain well.
Melt butter and apricot preserves in casserole and stir in lemon juice. Add vegetables; stir gently.
Sprinkle with parsley; put in moderate oven (350°) and bake until evenly glazed and heated through.

title: beef ole
directions: Brown beef.
Add chili powder and cumin dissolved in 2 teaspoons water.
Combine all ingredients and simmer uncovered for 30 minutes until sauce thickens.
Serve over bed of Fritos corn chips on dinner plate.
Garnish top with spoonful each of lettuce, chopped tomatoes, diced avocados, chopped onions, grated cheese and sliced ripe olives.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with butter and crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: real old fashioned lemonade
directions: In a large pitcher, combine lemon juice and sugar; stir to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.

title: great grandmother's gingerbread cookies
directions: In a saucepan, beat molasses and sugar until sugar melts.
Add soda dissolved in 1 teaspoon warm water.
Add the shortening and the spices.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter or knife.
