Bake pieces for 10 minutes at the most.
These burn very easily so keep an eye on the oven and the clock.
If cookies are too hard, put in a cookie jar with several pieces of dried fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam large head of broccoli and drain. Saute the onions. In saucepan, melt the 2 tablespoons butter and add the flour, salt and pepper. Add the milk. Stir and cook until bubbly. Reduce heat. Blend in the cream cheese until smooth. Place broccoli and onions in casserole dish. Pour sauce over vegetables. Top with cheese. Melt 2 tablespoons butter and toss with 1 cup soft bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: basted duck with oyster stuffing
directions: Season duck cavity and outside of bird with salt and pepper. To your favorite bread stuffing, add 1 cup oysters, drained and chopped.
Use oyster liquor as a part of liquid to moisten stuffing.
Lightly stuff duck; put the remainder of the stuffing in a pan to bake with duck (baste with duck drippings).
Place duck on a rack in a roasting pan; cover and bake in a slow oven (325°) about 2 1/2 hours.
Remove cover to brown.
Baste often with mixture of butter, lemon juice, paprika and thyme.

title: oriental cashew crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in large pan, set aside.
Combine remaining 4 ingredients in small bowl; quickly pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 10 cups.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add lemon juice, beaten egg yolks and salt.
Stir in milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Trim brisket and place in foil-lined pan (tear foil long enough to completely cover and seal around brisket). Mix together 1 bottle liquid smoke, garlic powder, onion powder and celery salt or seeds. Pour over brisket and seal foil around brisket. Refrigerate and let marinate overnight or at least several hours. Bake at 275 in foil for 5-6 hours (you can't hardly overcook it). Drain juices off and slice thin. Pour barbecue sauce over top of slices, cover with foil and bake about another hour.

title: honey cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Add coffee, honey and remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in tube pan. Makes two loaves.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown beef in hot oil over medium heat.
Add onions, cabbage and celery.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Add water; simmer over low heat 15 minutes.
Add beans, tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer over low heat 15 minutes.

title: cheesy corn dip(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 3 cups.
Great served with "Bugles" or baked tostadas.
Has 18 calories and approximately 1 g fat per tablespoon.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Put ingredients into a casserole.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: oven german pancake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients with a wire whip.
Melt butter in glass dish.
Bake at 450° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes with apricot glaze
directions: Cook sweet potatoes 45 minutes.
Let cool, peel and cut in 1/3-inch slices.
Grease 2-quart baking dish; set aside.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, honey or syrup and oil.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peggy's macaroni and cheese
directions: Grate cheese, set aside.
Drain liquid off tomatoes and chop them up.
Cook macaroni, drain well.
Mix everything together until cheese is melted.
Eat hot.
Salt to taste.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed overnight in milk and vanilla.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix poppy seed mixture with sugar and butter mixture.
Next, mix in flour mixture.
Beat 3 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes in two 9-inch cake pans.

title: curried seafood salad
directions: Early in day:
In large bowl, stir mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Add tuna, shrimp, celery and peas; toss well. Refrigerate covered.
In medium bowl, toss rice with Italian dressing; refrigerate covered.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Bring 2 1/2 cups milk to boil.
While heating, mix together the following:
egg yolks, sugar, salt, flour and 1/2 cup milk.
When milk comes to a boil, gradually add egg-sugar mixture with milk at low to medium heat.
Bring to boil and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, until mixture becomes thickened.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and butter.
While chilling, beat egg whites, adding 1 tablespoon ice water and a pea sized amount of cream of tartar to whites.
Beat until stiff.
Be sure egg whites were at room temperature.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla to stiffened whites. Chill pudding to room temperature.
Place sliced bananas on bottom of crust, then add 1/2 pudding mixture, then second half of pudding over another layer of bananas.
Add meringue on pudding and brown slightly in 400° oven.
Chill for several hours before serving. (Can also skip meringue and top with whipped cream and added sliced bananas.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Warm potatoes; drain juice.
Cream margarine, eggs and sugar. Add milk and spices.
Mash potatoes and add to mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips.
Wash well and pat dry.
Deep fry at 400° for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy.
Drain.
Combine Durkee red hot sauce, butter and Worcestershire sauce in bowl.
Toss wings in sauce to coat completely.
Serve with celery sticks and Blue cheese dressing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, spread the apples evenly.
Sprinkle with the water, cinnamon and salt.
In a small mixing bowl, mix the sugar, butter and flour with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Spread the mixture over the apples.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add liquid and boil until thickened.
Add butter, salt, pepper and diced, sliced or small whole beets.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Make sauce from cheese and milk.
Add crackers to butter.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish in layers, ending with crumbs.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: best pumpkin bread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar, add oil and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mix well.
This will make 3 loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: maple fudge
directions: Stir over medium heat until sugars are dissolved.
Continue cooking until soft ball stage.
Stir well to prevent sticking to pan.
Remove from heat; cool without stirring for a few minutes. Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: secret cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375° until good and brown, about 40 minutes.
You can also add corn, chopped jalapenos, green chilies or onion.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large pan, cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Add mushroom soup, water chestnuts, almonds and 1 cup of the cheese. Pour into large casserole and top with remaining cheese.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add stuffing and stir to moisten.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and top is browned.

title: wilma's party pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff.
Mix crackers, nuts, baking powder and vanilla.
Fold cracker mixture into egg whites.
Put into ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
While slightly warm, spread whipped cream or Cool Whip on top of pie.
Top with semi-sweet chocolate.
Serve chilled.
Can be made ahead.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix salad dressing and cream cheese.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese and blend.
Cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Shape into ball and roll in almonds.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Spray 3-quart casserole dish with nonstick spray (Pam). Sprinkle with chili peppers and cheese; set aside.

title: pineapple casserole(usually placed with vegetables)
directions: Drain the pineapple and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese and sprinkle over pineapple.
Top with 1/2 stack Ritz crackers (crushed, approximately 1/2 to 1 cup crushed) that has been mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Spread cream cheese out on a plate.
Use about 1/2 bottle of cocktail sauce.
Spread over cream cheese.
Sprinkle shrimp over all and pour rest of sauce over shrimp
or mix with the shrimp and spread.
Eat on crackers.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes and run through a sieve.
Put tomatoes back into a large pot and cook all ingredients but the tomato paste together for about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Then add tomato paste and simmer for 30 more minutes.
Put into hot jars, leaving 1/2 inch or more head room, and seal.

title: egg drop soup(light, sherry-flavored soup with the tang of scallion rounds)
directions: In a large soup pot, cook the onion and garlic in 3 tablespoons of the chicken stock.
When the onions are wilted, add the barley and the remaining stock.
Cook together on low heat for 25 minutes, covered.
Add the green pepper, cauliflower, zucchini and spinach and cook for 20 more minutes.
Stir in the tomato paste, thyme, dill, pepper and salt.
Continue stirring until the tomato paste dissolves.
Cook for 5 more minutes. Yields 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: strawberry pie with 7-up
directions: Sprinkle pie crust with sugar and bake to golden brown.
Line bottom of pie crust with strawberries.
In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add food coloring.
Pour over strawberries and refrigerate.
Once chilled, serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: seven layer taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Just before serving, top with 1 large jar of salsa.
Serve with nachos or tortilla chips.

title: brian bentley's savory spinach and rice soup
directions: In large saucepot, heat oil.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes or until soft, but not browned.
Add tomato puree, spinach, broth, tomato, rice, oregano and Tabasco sauce.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in chives.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Trim crust from bread and cut slices into 1/2 to 1/4-inch strips.
Melt peanut butter and mix with oil, garlic salt, paprika and hot sauce.
Brown bread and crust in 300° oven.
Mash crust into very fine crumbs.
Dip strips in peanut butter mix. Roll in crumbs.
Spread on paper towels and let dry overnight.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: For 5 to 6 servings you will need:

title: chili
directions: Fry and steam onion and green pepper.
Brown hamburger; put in pot.
Add all other ingredients to pot and simmer for 1/2 hour or longer.
Add water if needed.

title: peanutty snack mix
directions: Lightly butter a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch. Mix cereal, peanuts, raisins and banana chips in a large bowl. Mix pudding and pie filling (dry) and honey in a small saucepan. Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal mixture; toss until evenly coated. Spread in pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Makes about 10 cups of snack.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition.
Add eggs; beat until batter is smooth.
Stir in Amaretto, vanilla and melted butter.
In separate bowl, mix cornstarch and flour with just enough sour cream to make a smooth paste.
Add this paste and remaining sour cream to cheese mixture. Mix on low speed until thoroughly blended.
Pour into greased spring-form pan (9-inch).
Bake at 325° for one hour. Turn off oven and allow cake to remain in oven another two hours to cool gradually.
Cake will fall again with cooling.
Remove from oven when cool. Remove sides of pan, but leave cake on bottom. Refrigerate and serve in small servings as it is extremely rich and calorie laden.

title: cheese ball
directions: Melt sharp Cheddar cheese and Blue cheese in Pyrex dish in oven.
Drain grease.
Combine rest of ingredients, except nuts. Chill in ball.
Roll in chopped walnuts.

title: mint meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes before using.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar; beat until stiff.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating constantly. Add coloring (your choice) and flavoring.
Mix.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn the oven off.
Let stand in oven overnight or at least 5 hours.
Store in airtight containers.

title: karen's christmas candy
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Add chopped candy and stir.
Pour onto metal cookie sheet and flash freeze for 20 minutes.
Slice or break into brittle.

title: chicken cabbage salad
directions: Bake chicken and let cool.
Break up into small pieces.
Slice cabbage very thin.
Add onions, cashews and chicken.
Mix Oriental noodle spice packets, oil, vinegar and sugar.
Add 1/4 of sauce to salad and refrigerate.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove to paper towel to drain.
Crumble the bacon and save to add last.
Cook beef in fat remaining in skillet until no pink remains.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Combine beef, onion, catsup, salt, vinegar, mustard and brown sugar in a 3-quart baking dish. Partially drain all the beans and add to baking dish, stirring gently to mix.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter.
Beat well until fluffy add sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and freeze well.
Thaw 1 hour before serving.
Garnish with chocolate bar shaving.

title: white potato pie
directions: Bring water, salt and milk to boiling point.
Add instant potatoes and margarine.
Cool slightly, then add sugar, vanilla and beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake 35 minutes or until set (knife comes out clean when inserted in center).
Bake in a 400° oven.
Makes 3 (9-inch) pies.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger (uncooked) in bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Lay 6 tortillas on top of meat. Layer beans, onion, and cheese. Add 6 more tortillas on top. Spread soup over tortillas. Top with rotel tomatoes. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine and mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and apples.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil (375°).
Drain.
Sift powdered sugar over warm fritters.
Serve warm.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mash persimmons.
Mix nuts, raisins, persimmon pulp, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes in a greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff.
Crumble crackers coarsely.
Mix all ingredients (not including eggs) together.
Add to beaten egg whites.
Pour into 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients; pour over wings and marinate at least 1 hour (better overnight).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan.
Add all ingredients and then the shrimp.
Saute until shrimp turns pink and opaque, about 5 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Serves 4.

title: holiday special
directions: Combine flour, nuts and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, Equal and Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups whipping cream and let set.
Mix chocolate pudding with 1 1/2 cups whipping cream.
When set, can be mixed together or spread in layers on cheese mixture.
Let chill for 2 hours and Happy Holidays.

title: tomato sauce chicken
directions: Layer chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika. Drain tomatoes; reserve liquid.
Arrange onion slices, tomatoes and mushrooms over chicken.
Mix spices with tomato juice and pour over chicken.
Bake covered 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: basil cheese triangles
directions: Heat oven to 400. Grease cookie sheet. Crumble cheese into a small bowl; mash with fork. Stir in eggs, basil and white pepper until well mixed.

title: date roll nuts
directions: Mix well except nuts.
Cook until soft ball stage in cold water.
Add nuts; pour on wet towel and chill and then slice.

title: chocolate mallow cups
directions: Melt chocolate.
Put small amount in small paper cups in tart pan or miniature muffin tins.
Place a full teaspoon of Marshmallow Creme on top of chocolate.
Pour or spoon a little chocolate over Marshmallow Creme enough to cover.
Let set until cool and set. Great for holidays.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together cranberries and sugar; let set 20 minutes.
Drain cranberries and sugar mixture.
Add pineapple and marshmallows. Fold in whipping cream.
Garnish with nuts.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.

title: youth's favorite cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla, and salt.
Use cookie press to form cookies on baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order and pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° until set, about 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of brown sugar or less on batter.
Add 1/2 cup of pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
Mix in 2 cups fresh strawberries, sliced and sweetened to taste with Equal. Pour in graham cracker crust.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and layer sausage, bread and cheese in 9 x 13 pan. Mix together mushroom soup, eggs, mustard and milk.
Pour over other ingredients and bake for 350° for 1 hour. Top will be raised and slightly brown.
Best if fixed night before and baked in the morning.

title: low fat bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook potatoes until tender.
In another large saucepan, combine navy beans, chicken broth, water, ham, onion, celery, and carrots. Bring mixture to a boil. Stir in potatoes, garlic, pepper and salt.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix yeast and hot water; let stand 10 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese with butter.
Heat to very warm.
Mix with yeast; add egg, sugar, salt, onion, soda, dill seed and flour.
Go by stiffness of dough; you may add more flour.
Let rise until double in size. Knead down.
Put in loaf pan.
Let rise again.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan.
Brush with butter.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples thin; add 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and pour into pie shell.
Mix flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour on top of pie.
Cut margarine in pats and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Soften yeast in water and set aside.
Measure and sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and yeast; stir until well blended.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick and cut in biscuits.
Place on lightly greased pan and let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown. Brush tops with butter.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush wafers; melt margarine.
Add sugar, nuts and orange juice.
Mix all together.
Make into balls.
Roll in coconut. Refrigerate.
Very good and keeps a long time.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and cut chicken in bottom of 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix drained Veg-All and cream of chicken soup together and 1 cup broth. Pour over chicken.
Mix 1 cup milk and 1 cup Bisquick together. Pour over mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine the flour, soda, salt and apple pie spice. Combine and make a well for flour mixture the sugar, oil and eggs. Add the chopped apples last after cake is mixed. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the oleo and brown sugar.
Add the egg and vanilla.
Sift the flour with the baking soda and dash of salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Add the rhubarb.
Spread in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Top with topping.

title: apple yogurt treat
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 2.
Contains 185 calories, 6 gm fat and 81 mg sodium.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix
peanuts,
sugar and Karo syrup all together.
Boil for 15 minutes or until peanuts pop.
Add vanilla, baking soda and salt. Stir
well and pour into a well-greased pan or onto a piece of foil.
Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Add sugar to own taste.
Stir together and place in freezer for about 2 hours.

title: banana delight pie
directions: Prepare pudding with milk.
Set aside 1 cup filling.
Pour thin layer of remaining filling into cooled, baked 9-inch pie shell.
Slice bananas and arrange on filling.
Top with rest of filling.
Blend Cool Whip into measured filling.
Spread over filling.
Chill 3 hours.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on broiler pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Put into crock-pot with chili sauce and jelly.
Cook slowly for 2 to 3 hours.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin roll
directions: *May use 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg, 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 1 teaspoon ginger instead of pumpkin pie spice.

title: rosemary potatoes and onions
directions: Shake potatoes and onions in olive oil, salt and pepper. Layer in dish with rosemary sprigs between every 2 layers (or every layer if strong rosemary flavor is desired).
Dot garlic cloves around potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients well.
In separate bowl mix dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture alternating with milk to first bowl mixture.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam and lightly floured.
Top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 3-quart casserole with a nonstick vegetable coating. Set aside. Cook rice according to package directions, omitting margarine.
While rice is cooking, combine cream cheese and soup.
Mix until smooth and creamy. Add Cheddar cheese, onion and thawed broccoli.
Mix well. Add cooked rice and mix well.
Spoon into prepared pan and bake until top is golden brown, about 50 minutes.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: honey-nut snack mix
directions: Combine together cereal, oats, pecans, salt and cinnamon; then set aside.

title: aunt jane's boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil together lard, sugar, raisins, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Remove from stove and allow to cool.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Refrigerate heavy cream in a bowl with beaters for 1/2 hour. Mix instant coffee with vanilla and add to the chilled cream.
Add all the rest of the ingredients and beat until stiff to hold its shape.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add other ingredients and pour into 2 greased pie pans (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet, drain.
In bowl mix soup, water, rice, salt and pepper, and hamburger mixture.
Set aside.
Spray casserole dish with non-stick cooking spray on bottom and sides.
Evenly spread cabbage in casserole dish, pour soup mixture on top of cabbage, salt and pepper again.
Cover with casserole lid or aluminum foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, remove cover or foil and bake 1/2 hour or until topping becomes slightly crisp.
DO NOT over bake.

title: healthy cole slaw
directions: Combine yogurt, vinegar and honey in bowl large enough to hold cole slaw.
Stir until smooth and well blended.
Add vegetables and mix well.
Cover and chill for a minimum of 15 minutes.
Toss again before serving and drain liquid, if desired.
Use a slotted spoon to serve.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in buttered square pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix everything in order listed.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Can be baked in dish without pie shells.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Combine chicken, soup, tomatoes with chilies and tapioca. Line bottom of slow cooker with 1/3 chicken mixture, sprinkle with 1/3 onion and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover.
Cook on low for 6 - 8 hours.

title: breast of chicken and rice
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, buttered.
Place seasoned chicken on top and cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese.
Mix the confectioners sugar and cocoa.
Pour the melted cheese and margarine over the sugar and cocoa and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan (don't grease pan) and refrigerate.
Cut in pieces.

title: tomato chow chow
directions: Grind and
add
salt;
cover
with water and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Put in cloth bag; drip overnight.

title: caramel pecan dream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Mix at the highest speed until crumbly.
Press into the prepared pan.

title: biscochitos
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugar;
add eggs and anise seed. Cream well;
add rest of ingredients.
Add liquid, as needed, until mixture
holds together enough to roll.
Cut in desired shapes and dip in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: peach pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar and fill the pan with peaches.
Pour lemon juice on top.
Add butter or oleo and remaining sugar.
Cover with pastry.
Cut several gashes in the top to allow steam to escape.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix in oats and raisins. Combine egg, milk, vanilla and melted butter. Add to first mixture.
Stir only until ingredients are moistened. Drop dough by teaspoons on greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: Boil until it forms a firm ball when dropped into cold water. Place lid on pan with syrup and let stand until you beat egg whites with baking powder.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter and add brown sugar.
Stir over heat for 2 minutes.
Then add milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Slowly add confectioners sugar until smooth and of a spreadable consistency.

title: cranberry delight salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice and water in a 2-quart saucepan; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; add gelatin and stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce, lemon juice, lemon peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Add sour cream; stir until thoroughly combined.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into an 8-cup mold or serving dish.
Chill until firm. Keeps well.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Cook water and rice; fry chicken until lightly browned.
Pour ingredients into pan with chicken.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Make ring of rice on platter.
Put chicken mixture in center.

title: creamy cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large pot.
Add water; cook until onion is tender.
Place frozen broccoli in onion water.
Add salt and pepper.
Add the noodles, cream of chicken soup, the milk and cheese slices.
Simmer for a few minutes; stir often.
Can be frozen for later use.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven 400 degrees.
In large bowl beat eggs, add sugar, salt, nutmeg, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend hot milk, and pour into one 9-inch inch pie crust.
Bake 26 - 30 minutes or until knife placed in the center can come out clean.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Brown beef (cut in 1/2-inch strips) in oil. Add onions.
Cover and let cook about 30 to 40 minutes.
Add garlic, water and cornstarch.
Let simmer 30 minutes more.
Now add mushrooms and heat well. Serve over the rice.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello and hot water; set aside to cool.
When cool, fold in strawberries and Cool Whip.
Pour into a bowl.
Can use another box of fresh halved strawberries to decorate top of salad.

title: creole shrimp salad - new orleans
directions: Combine shrimp, rice, cauliflower, green pepper, pimiento and green onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Pour mayonnaise and sliced olives over this mixture.
Toss until blended.
Taste for seasoning.
Serve in lettuce cup.
Garnish with ripe olives and green onions.

title: midnight cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, salt and eggs.
Add cocoa, milk, flour and water.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: illinois meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° oven.
I always mix my meat loaf and refrigerate overnight or freeze.
This gives it more flavor.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter and place 1/2 mixture in greased dish.
Put chicken on crackers in dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and broth together.
Pour over chicken.
Top with remaining cracker crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, add water, tomatoes, taco seasoning and beans. Heat and serve with; your choice of avocados, corn dips cheese, onion or sour cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: In frying pan melt butter; add green pepper and onions.
Saute until soft.
Add flour, corn, milk and salt.
Stir into casserole dish.
Stir in cracker crumbs with butter; spread on corn mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter, and vanilla. Add sugar gradually. Cream until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs. Mix flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, cloves, and nutmeg. Mix well and add oats. Stir into creamed mixture alternating with milk. Add nuts, dates or raisins if desired. Spoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in 375 degree oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix well and spread in cookie sheet (with sides).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple in bottom, then spread cherry mix on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of cherry mix.
Next, sprinkle on chopped pecans.
Cut margarine in thin slices and put over entire mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Very good, served with ice cream.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Melt chocolate chips over double boiler in coffee.
Set aside. Mix cream cheese.
Add sugar gradually.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour and blend in heavy cream.
Add chocolate mixture.
Blend well.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven; open door and let sit for 1 hour to cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in pie dish and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix the next ingredients together and sprinkle over apples: brown sugar, oatmeal, melted butter and flour.
Leave uncovered and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Add chopped pimiento, bell pepper, celery, and onion rings.
Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add salt and Wesson oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let marinate for 24 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: taco navajo(modern)
directions: Grate cheese.
Shred lettuce; chop tomatoes and chilies. Brown lamb in lard.
Divide onto 6 fry bread.
Top with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, chilies and onions.
Serve with salsa!

title: mott's family crab cakes
directions: Mix and make into cakes.
When you mix the crab into the mixture, try not to break apart the crab.
You want the crab to stay in large lumps.
Makes 6 large cakes.

title: mexican red beans
directions: Put soaked and drained beans into crock-pot.
Add water and all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on High for 2 hours, then turn down to low for 8 hours.

title: peach-apricot delight(uncooked ice cream)
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar, apricot nectar and peaches. Pour into freezer can and add milk to fill line.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: aebleskiver (dutch treat)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add water and food coloring or Kool-Aid.
Stir well.
Put everything in a nonstick cooking pot. Cook slowly.
Keep on stirring until well blended.
Play dough is done when it doesn't stick to the pan.
Cool and knead.
Store in an airtight container.
You can freeze or refrigerate for months.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain pineapple, but leave some juice.	Place jello in drained pineapple and mix until jello is dissolved.
Add carton of cottage cheese, mixing well, then add drained mandarin orange slices. Fold in Cool Whip.	Place in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
It is better next day or needs all day to firm.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken slowly in hot shortening.
Add 1 cup water, bouillon and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well, cover and simmer until tender.

title: chili beans
directions: Soak pintos overnight; drain.
Brown ground chuck; drain. Place all ingredients in pot; mix together.
Stir occasionally and cook on low temperature for 5 hours.
This recipe freezes very well.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Brown chicken in skillet with minimal use of oil (corn oil best).
Add celery, mushrooms, water, ginger and broth mix. Cover; bring to a boil, then simmer until the chicken is tender, about 20 minutes.
Stir in snow peas.
Add soy sauce and blended cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened.
Makes 4 generous servings.
May be served over rice or chow mein noodles.
Very low calories if served alone.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix and add 1 box Jiffy cornbread mix. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add the cornmeal and cook until thick.
Add salt, baking powder, sugar and butter.
Beat the egg yolks and add to cornmeal mixture.
Beat the egg whites to a soft peak and fold into the batter.
Pour into a well-buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake uncovered in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Grits may be substituted for the cornmeal.
This recipe may be cut in half but use 2 eggs.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Blend Oreos (a few at a time) in a blender.
Set aside.

title: chicken and grape salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill several hours.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with cantaloupe, peaches or strawberries.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, folding in the stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Drop mixture into a well-greased and crumbed pan and bake in moderately hot oven or steam the mixture. The eggs may be omitted using 1/4 cup less milk.
Serve with white sauce.

title: lo-cal french fries
directions: Cut each potato into 8 wedges.
Spray the wedges generously with vegetable spray and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, turning once.

title: easy donuts
directions: Heat Fry Daddy until oil is hot.
Drop in biscuits.
Place on paper towel.
Roll in confectioners sugar and cinnamon.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding grated cheese last.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: babka
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder which have been sifted together.
Then add sour cream and beat together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in a greased and floured small Bundt pan.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients and pour into baking dish. Mix and blend the next 4 ingredients.
Spread on potato mixture. Blend by hand.
Bake until topping is light brown (approximately 30 minutes) at 350°.

title: peg's easy pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, eggs and salt. Add pecans. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350 degrees until golden and toothpick test to center comes out clean.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, mixed with cocoa.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift flour with salt and add 1/2 cup nuts to flour.
Mix together.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Scatter 1/4 cup nuts on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinade and baste for grilled chicken
directions: Brush on chicken while grilling.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn okra creole dish
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil for 5 minutes.
Add corn and okra; cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, thyme, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture. Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross balls with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator. Serve cold.

title: mexican fireballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese and olives.
Make one-inch balls.
Stuff with olives.
Roll in cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° on a shallow pan or cookie sheet.
May freeze before baking.
Thaw to bake.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until dissolved.
Cool.
Combine kraut and vegetables with vinegar mixture.
Makes four cups.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli. (Or follow package directions for microwave cooking.)
Mix all other ingredients with this in 2-quart baking dish. Bake 50 minutes at 325°, uncovered.
Top with cracker crumbs the last few minutes of baking.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and roll into balls.
Press down balls 2 ways with fork (to make them flat because they don't spread when baking).
Bake at 400° until tops are lightly brown.

title: coconut pecan german chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, including icing, and bake in Bundt pan at 350° about an hour.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into balls and chill. Melt chocolate chips and wax.
Dip balls and let cool.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute potatoes and onion in margarine in a large skillet over low heat 3 to 4 minutes or until most of the margarine is absorbed.
Add water and milk. Cook over low heat until potatoes are tender and sauce thickens, about 25 to 30 minutes. Stir occasionally. Add salt and pepper. Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: maine lobster stew
directions: Thaw lobster tails by separating them and setting out (room temperature) for approximately 4 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter with powdered sugar and half and half until smooth. Spoon into cooled pie shell.
Beat margarine with sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add egg and beat until very light. Beat in chocolate and spread over peanut butter. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream and chopped roasted peanuts.

title: chicken breasts with fontina, mushrooms and prosciutto
directions: Dredge the chicken lightly in the seasoned flour.
In a large skillet, heat the butter over moderately high heat until the foam subsides and in it, saute the chicken for 3 minutes per side, until it is browned lightly.
Transfer the chicken to a plate and keep warm.
Add the mushrooms to the skillet and saute them over moderately high heat for 1 minute.
Add the wine; bring the liquid to a boil, stirring, and boil the mixture, scraping up the brown bits, for 1 minute.
Add the chicken with any accumulated juices and Prosciutto; simmer the mixture, covered, for 5 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and season it with salt and pepper.

Transfer the chicken with tongs to a flameproof baking dish; top it with the Fontina and put the dish under a preheated broiler about 2 inches from the heat for 1 minute or until the Fontina is melted and browned lightly.
Transfer the chicken breasts to plate and spoon the Prosciutto mushroom sauce over them.
Serves 2; doubles/triples well.

title: uncooked barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved. Store in covered container in refrigerator until ready to use. Shake well before using.
Keeps for three weeks.

title: dump me cake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in bottom of pan.
Pour in cherry pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer pineapple, then pour cake mix over pineapple (cake mix is dry).
Do not stir.
Cut butter in small pieces and cover the top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Substitute any pie filling.

title: homemade bailey's irish cream
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Shake or put in blender. (Instead of the pint of all purpose I use 1 quart of half & half and enough heavy cream to make a 1/2 gallon of Irish Cream.)

title: strawberry yum-yum
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
In another dish, mix Dream Whip according to package directions.
Mix both mixtures together.

title: spinach and bacon salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together; let stand for several hours. Carefully pick over spinach removing stems and dead leaves.
Wash well and drain until dry.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
In remaining drippings, very quickly fry bread cubes until lightly browned.
When ready to serve, pour dressing over salad and toss well.
Sprinkle bacon, croutons and chopped eggs over top.
Yields 6.

title: old-fashioned southern corn pudding
directions: Cut kernels from cobs to yield about 3 1/3 cups corn.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add corn, green pepper and onion. Cook and stir for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: crisp peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugars together in bowl. Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together over margarine mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Refrigerate dough until well chilled.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with floured bottom of glass or with floured fork.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix half and half with soup; blend well.
Add sour cream; blend well.
Add 1/2 cup crumbs, green onions, cheese, salt and pepper to hash browns.
Melt 1 stick butter or margarine in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Pour mixture into dish and sprinkle other 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until bubbly and brown.

title: fat free apple dip
directions: Mix together.
Makes a great dip.
It's a wonderful substitute for caramel dip.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Wash and trim, leaving stems.
Pack into hot jars.
Add 1 clove garlic and 1/2 teaspoon salt to each pint.
Fill jars to overflowing with boiling vinegar.
Wipe off sealing surface. Seal.
Let stand several weeks.
Chill in refrigerator several days before serving.

title: low-sodium chicken with tarragon
directions: Flatten each breast piece by placing it between 2 sheets of wax paper and pound it until it's 1/4 inch thick.
Place pieces in a gallon plastic bag.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over chicken in bag.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Rotate bag once or twice.
Grill or broil chicken over medium heat 20 to 30 minutes until thoroughly cooked. Turn and brush chicken with additional marinade every 5 minutes while they cook.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: snack shake
directions: Place ice cubes in blender, until 1/2 full.
Pour in milk until 2 inches from top of blender, pudding mix, fruits and seasonings.
Blend on high until smooth.
Instant pudding thickens drink.

title: lemon layered delight(better known as dominos and jalapenos)
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and pecans.
Press flat in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 container Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix lemon pudding with 3 cups milk.
Spread over cream cheese.
Cover with second carton of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and chill thoroughly.

title: crockpot pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops on high until golden brown.
Remove from frying pan and place in crockpot.
When finished with pork chops, heat the 2 cans of cream of chicken soup, pour over pork chops. Add water until pork chops are covered, then stir.
Let cook on low 5 to 6 hours.
Can be served over rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Crumble bacon or sprinkle bacon bits on top before serving, if desired.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Mix mustard, olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper to make a paste. Place 4 salmon steaks, skin side down, in baking dish sprayed with Pam. Spread on mustard paste. Bake at 450° approximately 8 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with fresh dill.

title: antipasto squares
directions: Spread 1 package rolls on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer meat and cheese in order given.
Top with peppers.
Pour most of egg mixture on top.
Top with second package of rolls.
Brush with rest of egg mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until set in center and brown on top.
Cool.
Serve at room temperature or warm.
Cut into squares.

title: pasta carbonara
directions: Cut bacon into pieces and cook in butter until clear. Heat milk in small pan, add bacon and butter mixture. Add vinegar, will turn milk to cheese. Simmer for 15 min., until sauce cooks smooth. Boil your favorite pasta, al dente. Drain and return to pan. Quickly throw in whipped eggs, bacon sauce and cheese. Add salt and pepper, garlic (if you like) toss and serve.
Serves 6-8.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Crush cookies in
blender.
Add melted butter/margarine and flavoring.
Press into pie plate.

title: lentil soup
directions: Fry bacon and onion until golden brown.
Add carrots, celery and potato.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Add peeled tomatoes, lentils and ham or sausage.
Add enough water to cover.
Let simmer for 4 hours.

title: honey-pecan cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add honey, salt, flour and vanilla, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Roll into balls and bake on greased baking sheets at 300° until light brown.
Cool before removing.

title: marinated tomatoes and mushrooms
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes (submerge in boiling water for 1 minute, then peel).
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Add garlic to oil; drizzle half of oil over tomatoes.
Sprinkle sparingly with 1 to 2 teaspoons of vinegar.
Rinse mushrooms; do not remove stems.
Slice lengthwise.
Arrange over tomatoes. Season with salt, pepper and remainder of oil.
Sprinkle with remainder of vinegar.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill well. Garnish with black olives.
Serves 10.
Great for a cookout!

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoons into 350° hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: warm spinach salad(healthful eating)
directions: In a small saucepan, combine soy sauce, Sake, sesame oil and sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Put spinach and mushrooms into a salad bowl.
Toss with warm dressing.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serve at once.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir good. It will keep a long time in refrigerator.
Stir each time you use it.

title: savory swiss steak
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: tuna salad sandwiches
directions: Finely chop apples, pecans and celery.
Drain water off the tuna.
Mix with the chopped fruit and nuts and the mayonnaise. Spread mixture on the bread to make sandwiches and cut in halves or quarters.

title: latkes a la cohn
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into chunks.
Peel onion and cut into small pieces.
Break one egg into blender; add potatoes and onion. Blend until smooth.
Empty into a colander to get rid of some of the liquid, then pour into a large bowl.
Add remaining two eggs, garlic, bread crumbs, baking powder and salt.
(Taste batter or first pancake to test for salt.)
Add pepper and paprika.
Stir well.
The batter should be thick enough so that it will hold its shape and won't run off a tablespoon.
If not, add more bread crumbs.

title: toffee
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in a heavy saucepan.
Add sugar and water.
Stir until well-combined.
Increase heat slightly and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly until mixture turns caramel-colored (8 to 10 minutes).

title: golden gate lasagna
directions: Day before or early in the day, cook sauce.
In hot oil, saute the onion.

Add beef and cook until red color disappears. Slice garlic; mash with salt. Add to meat with pepper, oregano, parsley, tomatoes, tomato sauce and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rolls
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over
shortening, sugar and salt. Blend and cool.
Add eggs and yeast (dissolved in warm water). Stir in flour.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: two bean and rice salad
directions: In a 1 1/2 qt. covered container combine cooked rice, pinto beans, black beans, peas, celery, onion, diced green chili peppers, and the 1/2 cup cilantro. Add the dressing to the rice mixture; toss gently to mix. Cover and chill up to 24 hours. To serve, transfer the chilled salad to a serving bowl. If desired, garnish with cilantro sprigs, and whole chili peppers. Makes 16 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Sprinkle salt (1 1/2 tsp.)
in bottom of skillet.
Heat.
Add ground chuck.
Brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, oregano and basil.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: rich and creamy cold cucumber soup
directions: Combine the butter and oil in a soup pot. Heat to melt the butter.
Add the onions and saute them over medium heat until soft not browned.
Add the sliced cucumbers and cook over low heat until tender.
This will probably take about 12 to 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Combine the flour, dill weed and paprika in a small bowl.
Stir to mix. Sprinkle on top of the cucumbers and then add the broth, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until the mixture begins to thicken slightly.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl of food processor fitted with the steel blade. With the machine running, slowly add the cream and process until mixture is pureed.
Taste and add salt and white pepper, if needed.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: Butter a large baking dish and sprinkle with half the vegetables.
Place fish on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place remaining vegetables on top, then bread crumbs.
Pour wine and melted butter over top.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: canned red beets
directions: If using store vinegar, use only 1 cup.
Cook beets, cut into bite size pieces.
Fill jar 3/4 full of beets, pour mixture over beets in jar.
Cold pack.

title: mushroom-cheese sauce
directions: Melt in saucepan the margarine.
Blend in the flour, salt, dry mustard and few grains cayenne pepper.
Heat until mixture bubbles. Remove from heat.
Add gradually while stirring constantly the 2 cups milk.
Return to heat.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 or 2 minutes longer.
Blend in 1/4 cup drained mushrooms.
Cool sauce slightly. Add the grated Cheddar all at once.
Blend sauce rapidly.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add rice and cook, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add meat, green onions, ginger and pepper.
Continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Push rice mix to side; break eggs into the middle of skillet and scramble.
Stir eggs into rice mixture.
Add soy sauce and sugar; cook, stirring for 1 minute.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add other ingredients, except sour cream. Jell half of the mixture, then add sour cream to the remaining half of the jello mixture and jell.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, cream of mushroom soup, onion, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and grated cheese.
Then pour in baking dish.
Crush up Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter.
Spread over top of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes more.
This freezes well.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: our favorite chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar, salt and butter.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Add flour, sifted with baking soda and cream of tartar, alternating with milk.
Beat well and pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: grandma's peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, sugar and milk; pour mixture into baking dish.
Spoon peaches over batter.
Pour 1/4 cup peach juice over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, flour and pecans. Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan to make a crust.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla well. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on crust and chill.
Spread blueberry pie filling on top.
Other pie topping can be used.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Dip in beaten egg and then coat with seasoned bread crumbs.
Heat frying pan with oil; place coated chicken in pan and brown.
Place in casserole.
Pour the spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be prepared the night before and baked the next day.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in butter 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tarragon and next 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook until it turns pink.
Add parsley.

title: sweetened whipped cream
directions: Beat on high speed until soft peaks form.
Makes 2 cups.

title: toffee(heath bars)
directions: Line jelly roll pan (smallest baking sheet) with Reynolds Wrap.
Cover with saltine crackers.
Boil sugar and butter exactly 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over mixture as chips melt.
Refrigerate.
Break into pieces.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheese bar squares
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with 1 package of crescent rolls.
Cream together cream cheese, egg yolk, first sugar and vanilla.
Spread on rolls.
Top with other package of crescent rolls.
Mix with a fork flour, second sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of rolls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 375° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Wash and drain blueberries.
Divide among individual serving dishes.
Mash banana very fine; blend in sugar and nutmeg.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over berries and serve.

title: quick mini pizzas
directions: Spread crackers out on a paper plate.
Top each one with a slice of pepperoni and a slice of cheese.
Microwave 10 to 15 seconds, just until cheese melts.
Children can prepare by themselves.
They love it.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut shortening in.
Add buttermilk. Dissolve yeast in water; add to mixture.
(Add extra flour, if needed.)
Stir.
Roll dough; cut into shapes.
Let rise 10 minutes before baking.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Can be put in plastic bags and frozen.
Will make 60.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and microwave until melted and onions are cooked.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once until thoroughly blended. Use 13 x 9-inch ungreased glass dish (the original recipe calls for a pan).
If you use a glass dish, check cake 5 minutes earlier to see if it's done.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip(low-fat recipe)
directions: Brown diced onion in chicken broth.
Add cooked ground turkey. Stir refried beans into turkey mixture.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Sprinkle green chiles over top of turkey-bean mixture.
Spread 1/2 of cheese over this.
Pour taco sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool slightly and spoon sour cream to make a cross on top of casserole.
Serve with low-fat tortilla chips.
Serves 32 (1/4 cup servings).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in margarine until tender. Add soup and milk; stir until smooth. Turn off heat and add spices, spaghetti, sharp cheese and chicken. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle Parmesan on top. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: cheese bites
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pinch off marble-size pieces.
Bake on greased baking sheet in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir together the eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add flour, grated zucchini and nuts. Bake in loaf pans (2 or 3) for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour in 9 x 14-inch pan for 10 minutes before cake is done.
Bring to a boil the sugar and milk.
When cake is done, punch holes in top with a fork. Immediately pour mixture over the cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fancy fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Serve with the following fruits: bananas, strawberries, mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks.

title: far east celery(good side vegetable)
directions: Slice and cook celery until just tender; drain.
Mix with next 3 ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Take 1 cup soft bread crumbs and toss with almonds and butter.
Spread over casserole. Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: snickers ice cream
directions: Chop up snicker bars, add to the other ingredients.
Add whole milk and freeze.
Do not fill milk to the freeze line.

title: macaroni with ham and broccoli
directions: Prepare macaroni as package directs.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover; bake for 55 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover; top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and walnuts. Stir until coating starts to harden. Spread on a greased cookie sheet to cool.
Makes 1 pound.

title: grape-nuts banana bread
directions: Mix flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in cereal. Combine banana, milk, egg and oil. Add flour mixture, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove and cool on rack.
Recipe may be doubled and tripled.
Best served the next day.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Measure sifted flour. Add sugar, then Crisco.
Cut shortening into flour.
Dissolve yeast in 1 1/2 cups warm water.
To flour mixture, add buttermilk and yeast.
Knead and roll out.
Cut as for biscuits.
Put butter or margarine on half of biscuit, then fold over other half.
Pinch edges.
Let stand and rise or bake at once.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: hershey's disappearing cake
directions: Generously grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.

title: sloppy "joses"
directions: Brown beef and vegetables in shortening.
Stir to separate meat into small particles, pour off fat; add soup and seasoning. Simmer to blend flavors.
Serve on buns.
Serves 6.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, celery and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Add water.
Bring to boil.
Add salt, carrots, potatoes and spices.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Add tomatoes.
Heat through and serve.

title: patsy's taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add Catalina dressing to taste. Add extra nacho cheese Doritos to keep crunchy.

title: chew cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients and bake in a long pan at 300° for 40 minutes or until good and brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made as muffins also.

title: quick scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour gradually.
Add salt and milk.
Stir constantly until thick.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes until melted.

title: south texas steak
directions: Trim steak.
Cut into 8 pieces and place in a nonmetallic dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Marinate for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Grill steak over hot coals 4 to 6 inches from heat, basting with marinade.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes per side for medium rare, 8 to 10 minutes per side for medium.
Heat remaining marinade and serve with steak.

title: tex-mex guacamole
directions: Halve the avocados lengthwise and scoop the flesh into a medium size bowl.
Add the lime juice and salt.
Mash with a fork, mixing well.
Add the green onions, tomato, garlic, green chili pepper and cilantro.
Blend well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: nutritious breakfast cookies
directions: Cream margarine, honey, eggs, vanilla and applesauce in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add wheat germ and mix well.
Blend in oats, dates, bran, nuts and milk.
Add to egg mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: colorful corn salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 12 ingredients (through cayenne pepper). In a microwave bowl, combine oil and garlic. Microwave on High for 1 minute. Cool. Whisk in lime juice. Pour over first mixture and toss to coat. Yields 16 to 18 servings. Cut in half for smaller crowd. Great with Mexican dishes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple (undrained); fold in marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Mix together ricotta cheese, sugar and eggs. Set aside. Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 baking dish. Carefully spoon ricotta mixture over batter. Bake at 350 for 50-60 minutes or until done. Sprinkle powdered on top before serving.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift confectioners sugar and cocoa into glass bowl. Pour melted margarine and milk on top, but do not stir yet. Put into microwave for 2 minutes on High. Take and stir. Add vanilla and stir well. Pour into greased Pyrex dish and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Then, sift together flour, salt and cinnamon.
Sprinkle about 1/4 of the flour mixture over the prepared pecans and gumdrops.
Beat eggs and water until light. Add gradually the brown sugar.
When sugar is well blended, stir in the flour mixture and, last, the nuts and gumdrops.
Spread the batter in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Ice the cake with confectioners sugar thinned to a good spreading consistency with lemon juice.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla and flour.
Mix together, then add: oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into golf ball size and place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Add all seasonings.
Stir in flour, add tomato sauce
and water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Break up tortillas, layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:
tortillas, sauce, olives. Repeat.
Top with cheese (shredded).
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: hershey's best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350. Grease 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. In large microwave safe bowl, place butter. Microwave at HIGH (100%) for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until melted. Stir in sugar and vanilla; add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended. Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well. Stir in nuts, if desired. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan. Cool completely in pan.

title: party mix
directions: Just mix them all together.
It's as easy as that!

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Shake all ingredients in a jar until well blended.
This is just as good as store bought.
(Maybe better.)
And most of the ingredients you'll already have on hand.

title: cream cheese-stuffed chicken
directions: Cut cream cheese lengthwise into 4 sticks.
Chill until ready to	use.
Place
chicken,
boned
side
up,
wrap with 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap and pound chicken out from center with
meat mallet to 1/8-inch thickness.
Remove wrap.
Sprinkle chicken with
salt	and
pepper.
Place 1 cheese stick on each piece
of chicken.
Fold in sides, and roll up, pressing ends to
seal.
Mix egg
and
water.
Mix crumbs and parsley. Coat chicken
rolls with
flour; dip in egg mixture.
Roll in crumb mixture
to
coat. Cover
and
chill	for
1 hour.
Fry chicken rolls
in
hot
oil about
minutes or until golden brown.
A
wok
works best, but a deep fryer or frying pan can be used.

title: garlic roasted chicken
directions: Carefully work fingers under skin of chicken around breast and legs.
Combine with butter, lemon peel, thyme, oregano and Italian seasonings.
Lightly season chicken all over with salt and pepper. Spread garlic butter under skin.
Broil chicken for 50 to 55 minutes.
Place chicken in oven at level below top rung.
Take care not to burn by putting aluminium foil on top for second 20 minutes. Set aside 2 teaspoons garlic butter.
Add a teaspoon water and use for basting.

title: son-in-law's favorite banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour in top of double boiler.
Blend in milk,
a
small
amount
at
a time.
Add 1 2/3 cups water. Cook, stirring
to
a boil.
Beat egg yolks.
Add egg yolks to hot mixture,
stirring	constantly.
Add
salt	and
vanilla; remove from
heat.
Cool custard for about 10 minutes.
Layer half the wafers, half of the bananas and the custard in dish. Repeat layers, ending with wafers.

title: raggedy robins
directions: Boil margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir and drop by spoon on waxed paper to cool.

title: italian brunch casserole
directions: Remove and discard casings from sausage.
Cook sausage in large skillet, stirring until sausage crumbles and is no longer pink; drain.
Add green onions and next 3 ingredients to skillet. Saut 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in roasted bell peppers; drain and cool.
Spread 4 cups of bread cubes in a lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Top with half each of the sausage mixture and cheese.
Repeat with remaining bread, sausage and cheese.
Whisk together eggs and milk.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour or until bubbly and hot.

title: chili beans
directions: Mix pinto beans, onion, ham substitute, garlic clove, salt and pepper.
Cook for 2 hours, then add hot sauce, green pepper, sugar and tomatoes.
Cook for 3 more hours.

title: rutabaga(northern turnips)
directions: Peel and slice rutabagas and place in saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 1 hour.
Drain in colander.
Add 1/2 cup margarine or bacon drippings.
Mash and serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Stir after the first hour.
Add some pineapple juice, if needed.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy in large mixing bowl. Mix on lowest speed of mixer until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie with candy Kiss after cookies have been removed from oven.
Press down firmly with candy Kiss, so cookie cracks.

title: cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add sugar, salt, and cheese all at once and the flour gradually, mixing well.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in bowl, cover, and let rise in a warm draft-free place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Knead dough again, cover, and let rise until doubled.
Place dough in 2 greased loaf pans; cover and let rise again until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Remove loaves from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hershey's syrup brownies
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Grease and flour 13 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lynda's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skins in microwave until soft but still a little firm.
Cool.
Peel and cut in chunks. Grate eggs.
Mix salt, pepper, onion, potatoes, radishes and eggs.
Mash any large chunks of potatoes.
Add mayo, mustard, pickles and juice.
Mix to desired consistency.
Chill.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour together until thick; refrigerate.
Cream together sugar, butter and Crisco.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Very good and not too sweet.

title: a family favorite strawberry jello salad
directions: Completely dissolve Jell-O in hot water in 9 x 13 dish. Add pineapple and strawberries to Jell-O and chill in refrigerator. When Jell-O mixture is completely set, spread topping on.

title: cheese salad
directions: Beat cheese with mixer.
Add other ingredients, mix well.

title: pinto bean pie(mock pecan)
directions: Combine sugar and spices; mix well.
Add beans, egg, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 minutes or until set.

title: italian pita crisps
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.

Brush margarine evenly over each pita half, sprinkle evenly with cheese mixture. Cut each pita half into 8 wedges and place on a baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 8 minutes or until crisp; let cool.

title: cottage cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add unbeaten eggs, beating thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk and vanilla.
Stir only until the ingredients are blended.

title: applesauce (no egg) cake
directions: Combine sugar and oleo; cream well.
Add flour and applesauce, alternately.
Add pecans and raisins, along with spices.
Bake for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: broiled crab melt-away
directions: Toast muffin halves.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread on muffins. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cut into quarters.
Freeze at least 2 days and up to 1 month.
Broil until golden before serving.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream butter and gradually beat in sugar and eggs. Combine dry ingredients. Add to egg mixture, alternating with yogurt. Stir in pears and vanilla. Pour into buttered 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot into a large bowl.
Mix sugar, salt, pepper, buttermilk, mayonnaise, vinegar and lemon juice in separate bowl.
I have found this makes plenty of dressing, you may not want to use all of it.
Mix the dressing well into the cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Will be even better the next day.

title: raspberry nut chocolate chunk chews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with foil and lightly butter it.
Set oven rack in center of oven.
Using a hand mixer beat brown sugar, sugar and baking soda on medium speed for about 15 seconds.
Add butter, egg, egg white, vanilla and zest; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes, or until smooth and light in color.
Scrape bowl and add jam; beating again on medium speed for about 15 seconds.
Add flour and chocolate all at once and beat on low speed just until flour is mixed in.
Spread dough into the prepared pan, smoothing the top.
Bake for 20 minutes, reversing baking pan halfway through baking time.
Top will be firm to the touch and light brown in color.
Remove pan from oven and set on wire rack to cool.
When completely cool, cut into bars.
Makes 24 - 2 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Separate into 2 equal parts. Roll between two pieces of wax paper.
Place in pie dish.

title: nellie's cake mix bar cookies
directions: Beat the cake mix briefly with the egg and butter, until just blended. Press into a 9x13 inch pan lightly coated with vegetable oil spray. Sprinkle the nuts and chocolate chips on to and lightly press into first layer. Beat together the confectioners sugar, eggs and cream cheese. Spoon over top, spreading mixture evenly to edges. Bake 1 hour to 1 hours, 15 minutes at 350° or until top is puffed and lightly browned. Cool and cut into bars. Makes 30 bars.

title: magic cookies
directions: Melt butter and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Crush graham crackers and spread over melted butter.
Add layer of chocolate chips and layer of coconut and layer of nuts.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creamy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat milk; add next 4 ingredients. Stir well until smooth.
Add potatoes.
Put in a casserole dish and heat until bubbling, about 30 minutes.

title: spritz(cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Put through cookie press.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice.
Brush 4 (6 ounce) ramekins with 1/2 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle sugar to coat.
In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs with remaining butter.
Add remaining ingredients to apples and toss.
Divide a third of the bread crumbs among the ramekins. Arrange half the apples over crumbs and another third of crumbs. Repeat with the rest of apples and crumbs.
Press into ramekins. Bake for 20 minutes.
Raise oven temperature to 450° and continue baking until top browns and apples are tender.
Cool 5 minutes, loosen with knife, then turn out on plate.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Heat milk in top of double boiler, then stir in cornstarch which has been mixed with a little cold milk.
Stir constantly until the mixture thickens.
Then turn heat very low.
Mix together egg yolks and sugar.
Beat until very light.
Combine this with cornstarch mixture.
Cook thoroughly, stirring occasionally, so that it won't lump.
Beat the egg whites stiff until they form peaks.
Beat in a deep bowl.
Pour the cornstarch mixture over the beaten egg whites.
Cover the whites completely. Sprinkle vanilla over the top.
Next, do not stir, fold the mixture.
The heat of the cornstarch seems to partially cook the egg whites.
Fold together gently until there are no more flecks of egg white visible.
Let stand in a warm room until cool.

title: raspberry rum ricki
directions: Blend with ice until thick. Garnish with lime.

title: "spaghetti sauce"(straight from italy!)
directions: Brown onion in little oil.
Then brown meat until loose.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, oregano, water, salt and sugar.
(For added flavor, add pork neck bones or ribs, pork chops or sausage, but first boil in separate pot for a few minutes to remove scum. Rinse under water and add to sauce.)
Before serving, remove any sizable pieces of meat and remove any bones.

title: three-bean baked beans
directions: *Make liquidy enough to allow for evaporation during baking or add water during baking if beans become dry.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, onion, chilies, sour cream and salt in saucepan. Heat until warm (do not boil).
Spoon a small amount of sauce into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Fill tortillas with chicken, sauce and cheese.
Roll up to enclose filling and arrange in prepared dish.
Top with remaining cheese and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion and drain. Grease a 3-quart casserole dish. Combine meat with the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1 (3 ounce) can Chinese noodles over top and bake 10 minutes longer. Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Put into quart jar.
Will keep in refrigerator indefinitely.
Dilute with cream when used.

title: cheese potatoes (low-fat)
directions: Spray a baking dish with Pam.
Mix the onion and potatoes together.
Spread potato mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and spread over potato mixture. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Slice top from each potato.
Scoop out centers and place in medium bowl.
Set shells aside.
Add milk, margarine and seasonings to potato and mash until fluffy. Stir in cheese.
Crumble bacon and add 2/3 to potato mixture. Spoon into potato shells and sprinkle tops with remaining bacon and the chives.
Place stuffed potatoes on serving plate. Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until potatoes are hot, rotating dish after half the cooking time.
