title: beef chimichanga
directions: Add small amount of each ingredient in the middle of a flour tortilla and roll into a 2-inch diameter size (makes a burrito). Deep-fry each burrito in light oil until brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Top each serving with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, chopped green onions (optional) and more grated cheese. Garnish with pitted ripe olives (sliced), avocados (optional) and sour cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Use a large mixing bowl.
Beat margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs and beat.
Add flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt and beat.
Add milk and beat.
Add additional flour and stir in with a spoon.
Divide into two or three parts and wrap in tinfoil.
Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready to bake, roll out on floured surface 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin pans. Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar, oil and pumpkin. Beat thoroughly. Add dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Stir in raisins.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and sprinkle tops with brown sugar. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 24 muffins.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Carefully wash strawberries, leaving greens intact.
Pat dry. Melt chocolate chips in microwave, stirring occasionally until thoroughly melted.

title: quick gazpacho *
directions: Put canned tomatoes in freezer to chill while preparing vegetables.
Cut peeled and seeded vegetables into large chunks. Put undrained tomatoes in food processor or blender and puree until smooth.
Add garlic, cucumber and green pepper and process until still slightly lumpy.
Stir in vinegar and Tabasco sauce.
Cover and chill in refrigerator until time to serve.
Makes 2 or 3 generous servings.

title: hurried housewife chili
directions: Brown the ground meat in a large pan.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer until chili thickens to desired consistency, or 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes a very good, quick meal for 8 to 12 people.

title: ruby ross cherry salad
directions: Beat cherries with mixer to cut into small pieces. Add Eagle Brand, then add Cool Whip. Add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: toss-up salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix noodles, tuna, cucumbers, tomatoes, celery, green peppers and green onions.
In another bowl, blend Italian dressing, mayonnaise and spices.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill.
Toss again before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about one hour.

title: indian summer salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice, pineapple and oranges.
Pour into 8 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Prepare topping by mixing Dream Whip and pudding according to directions on individual boxes.
Fold together and spread on top of gelatin.
Chill.
Serves 12.
Delicious!

title: battle of the bulge(scrumptious strawberry drink for calorie controlled diets)
directions: Whiz up all ingredients in a blender and serve in a glass decorated with a strawberry on a cocktail stick.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: May use 1 teaspoon lemon if desired.

title: chicken broccoli(gloria earnshaw)
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Spread broccoli on bottom and chicken on top.
Add soup and onions (mixed).
Put bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour until bubbly.

title: light crab spread
directions: Finely chop onion.
Press garlic.
Mix onions, garlic, cheese and milk until well blended.
Spread in baking dish.
Coarsely chop tomato and green pepper.
Snip the parsley.
Mix together tomato, green pepper, 2 tablespoons of parsley, lemon juice and salt. Spoon on top of cheese mixture.
Top with crabmeat.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Chill.
Serve with bread or fresh veggies. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Mix last four ingredients and add hot dogs.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve in chafing dish.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter reese's
directions: First Layer:
Mix melted oleo, crumbs, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Put in an ungreased oblong cake pan.

title: moravian molasses cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the brown sugar, margarine, Crisco and molasses.
Heat until brown sugar is dissolved. Dissolve the baking soda in the boiling water and stir into the molasses mixture.
The mixture will bubble up.
Remove from heat.

title: lacy kern's beet salad - molded
directions: Simmer first seven ingredients.
Strain out cloves.
Add sugar. While mixture is still quite hot, pour over jello.
Add gelatin. Put in beets.
Mold in ring mold or individual molds.
Garnish with lettuce, cheese balls (small), artichoke hearts, etc.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Add all ingredients except cheese and pepperoni and mix well. Put 1/2 of mixture in baking dish.
Add 1 cup cheese and layer with pepperoni, and then repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boy scout recipe for carp
directions: Use a 12-inch pine board, cleaned well.
Butter the board all over.
Clean carp and place on board.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf, parsley and thyme to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done to a golden brown, remove from oven.
Carefully remove carp from board.
Throw the carp away and eat the board.

title: golden potato squares
directions: Pare potatoes and place immediately in cold water.
Saute onion in butter in skillet until tender.
Add evaporated milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper in a large glass bowl; beat until frothy.
Shred potatoes using medium blade of shredder.
Place immediately into egg mixture, turning to coat well.
Add parsley, 1 cup of cheese and milk mixture; mix well. Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Top with 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake 30 more minutes or until done.
Cut in squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Spread pie filling in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fish herb mix
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in an airtight container. Use to sprinkle over fish or chicken and cook as desired.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar until clear.
Grind green pepper finely. Pour into vinegar and boil 1 minute.
Turn off heat and cool.
Add one 6 ounce bottle Certo and 6 or 7 drops green food coloring. Pour into sterilized jelly jars; seal with paraffin.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, sugar and margarine.
(Double for thicker crust.)

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease and flour 10 inch tube pan.
In a large bowl mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until mixed. Hand mix only.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool on rack 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Brown and drain sausage well. Mix Cheddar cheese soup and water until smooth. Stir in sausage and Bisquick. Fill greased muffin tin 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in microwave on high for 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour mixture over Crispix and stir lightly.
Place confectioners sugar in small size trash bag and add cereal.
Shake bag gently until cereal is coated with sugar.
Place in tight container.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar with 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Mix and put in greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and pour melted butter over them. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can leave off crumbs; turn upside-down on serving tray and serve on Ritz crackers like a cheese ball.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets whole with peeling and stems on.
Peel and cut as desired; leave whole, slice or cut in quarters.
Bring water, vinegar, spices and salt to a boil; add beets.
Bring back to a boil, then place beets in sterilized jars and seal.
May use canned beets.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with sour cream. Beat mixture until smooth. Pour in taco seasoning mix and beat again for approximately 1 minute. Place into serving dish (small). Top with shredded cheese. Also good topped with chopped tomatoes, salsa, refried beans, chopped black olives and mild peppers.

title: grandma's tuna supreme salad
directions: Mix all together and place in refrigerator; chill.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the flour, oats, sugars, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nuts and chocolate chips.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in 4 1/2 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain.
Serves 6.

title: brunede kartofler(danish sugar-browned potatoes)
directions: Wash potatoes and cook in skin until tender (in salted boiling water), but not falling apart.
Drain when cool, peel off skins.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread butter on one side of each bread slice.
Stack slices and cut in 3/4-inch squares.
Turn into ovenproof 1-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with sugar, raisins and spice.
Beat egg with milk.
Pour over bread mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until pudding is set.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken 1 hour at 350°, then cut into small pieces.
In greased casserole layer starting with chicken, then broccoli, then sauce made up of mixture of last 4 ingredients, then cheese.
I usually get 2 sets of layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Not in recipe, but good with water chestnuts and carrots added.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions together until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Croutons on top (optional).

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix crackers and butter.
Press into pie plate. Bake 5 minutes.
Saute onions in oil, then arrange over crust.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over onions. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Delicious!

title: don't tell them it's butterscotch
directions: Combine and beat cake mix with pudding and eggs.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar, chocolate chips and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mama ables' junk
directions: You will need 2 pans, 1 for the meat and onions and 1 for the potatoes (1 frying pan and 1 large pot or Dutch oven).

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add the moist.
Stir.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas to creamed sugar and margarine.
Then add dry ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in loaf pan.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Add scalded milk to salt, sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat well and let rise until very light.
Add egg yolks and remaining flour. Knead lightly.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness and cut into rounds.
Set these close together on a greased pan and let rise.
Glaze the surface of each bun with a little egg white diluted with water.
With a sharp knife, cut a cross on top.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Just before removing from the oven, brush with sugar and water.
Fill the cross with plain frosting when cooled.
May also be baked in round loaves.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter and sugar; beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Combine all ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead lightly 6 to 8 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: mother's one pot spaghetti
directions: Cook beef and onion in very large skillet over medium heat, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink. Drain off any fat. Return beef to skillet. Stir in broth, tomato paste, salt, oregano, garlic powder and pepper. Bring to a boil. Add uncooked spaghetti. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring often, for 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: david's yummy oat bran muffins(no fat added!)
directions: You will need foil muffin cups.

title: banana muffins
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed with electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg, vanilla and butter flavorings, beating until blended.

title: margie's mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Put in bowl and cool.
Cream butter and shortening 4 minutes.
Add sugar gradually and beat 4 more minutes.
Add flour paste and beat 4 minutes more.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: marinated duck breast
directions: Fillet duck breasts on each side.
Slice filleted breasts into strips 1/2-inch wide and 3 to 4-inches long.
Put strips, Italian dressing, jalapeno slices and garlic salt in plastic bag. Refrigerate for 24 to 36 hours.

title: herbed bread twist
directions: In a small bowl, combine seasoning, garlic powder, salt and pepper flakes. Separate strips of dough and arrange on a baking sheet. Brush tops with egg and sprinkle with mixture. For each twist, hold one end in each hand. Turn ends in opposite directions to make spirals. Return to baking sheet, pressing gently on each end to hold in place. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 12.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Press 1 package of crescent rolls into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cheese mixture and cover with other package of crescent rolls.
Beat egg white until foamy; spread egg white on top.
Sprinkle almond slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sole and vegetables joanne
directions: Lightly butter 4 individual ramekins.
Pat fillets with paper towels.
Cut each fillet in half crossways, roll from cut side and fasten with a wooden pick.
Place seam-side down in a cold 10-inch skillet.
Mix wine, carrots, celery, green onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Over medium heat, cover and bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer for 6 minutes, until fish barely flakes with a fork.
With a spoon, remove fish and place in ramekins; keep warm.
Remove vegetables from skillet; set aside.
Reserve 1/4 cup of the liquid and set aside; discard remaining liquid.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break bread into quarters and place in 9 x 11-inch cake pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle raisins over bread.
Beat eggs, dry milk, sugar and vanilla for 2 minutes. Pour over bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onion and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Stir in flour with a wire whisk.
Pour about 1 inch of oil in large skillet and heat to 375°.
Dip onion rings, a few at a time, into batter, then fry 3 to 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
If batter is too thick, add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.

title: baloo's chicken noodle soup with vegetables
directions: Pour soup into saucepan.
Add 1/2 can of water.
Stir.
Add a can of mixed vegetables with their juice.
Stir.
Cook soup over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Eat with favorite crackers.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: jello fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add box of Jell-O and cool.
Place fresh or frozen fruit in pie shell.
Pour sauce over fruit.
Chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: jill's meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.	Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put first 5 ingredients
in a large bowl and set aside. In a heavy saucepan
mix
and
cook
the
milk,
margarine and sugar. Boil over medium
heat for 10 minutes, stirring almost constantly. Pour over
ingredients
in the mixing bowl.
Stir together, mixing well.
Pour
in large, buttered dish.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil fryer in seasoned water.
Cook spaghetti in fryer water. Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add soup, cheese and pimentos to vegetables.
Add deboned chicken.
Pour sauce over spaghetti and mix well.
Season to taste.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain on paper towel.
Combine tomatoes and cheese in top of double boiler.
Cook over water until melted, then add cooked sausage.
Serve hot.

title: sweet-sour beef balls with pineapple
directions: Mix beef, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt, onion and pepper; form into small balls.
Brown in small amount of oil; drain.
Add pineapple juice to oil; heat.
Add mixture of remaining cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, water and sugar.
Cook until juice thickens, stirring constantly.
Add meat balls, pineapple and green peppers; cook until they are slightly cooked but still crunchy.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar well. Add egg yolks. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Fold in egg whites. Add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook the celery, onion and carrots together until done; drain. Mix all ingredients, except biscuits, together and put 1/2 the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with 1 can biscuits.
Brown in a 350° oven, then put in remaining mixture and cover with the other can of biscuits.
Return to the oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers.
Cut in half lengthwise - clean seeds and membrane. Precook peppers in boiling salt water 5 minutes.
Place peppers into 10 x 8 glass baking dish.
Salt inside of peppers.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt the oleo in the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Then add the graham crumbs, condensed milk, chocolate chips, coconut and walnuts.
Layer recipe in baking dish.
Press down with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until coconut is light brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine graham crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and softened butter. Press firmly into bottom of tube or spring-form pan (coating sides of pan with butter helps).
Beat cheese until soft.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Gradually add one cup sugar and mix well. Stir in one teaspoon vanilla and pour carefully into pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until inserted knife comes out clean. Let cool 10 minutes. Spread over top a mixture of sour cream, 5 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Bake 5 minutes longer. Cool. Place in refrigerator until set. Cut in small servings.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash, onion and carrots until almost done, approximately 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix the soup, sour cream, salt and pepper; add to squash mixture.
Grease a 2-quart casserole well with butter.
Layer squash with stuffing mix.
Dot with butter and end up with stuffing mix on top layer.
Bake. Serves 8 to 10.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil. Add flour, baking soda and salt slowly mixing in with the buttermilk. Mix well, then add raisins and Raisin Bran. Stir in well. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in lined muffin tins. The batter will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: party chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts in a greased pan and sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Mix soup, cream cheese and sour cream.
Cover chicken with soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours in a 300° oven.
Uncover and bake at same temperature for an additional hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, three fourths of the brown sugar substitute, milk, egg, melted margarine and vanilla; stirring until well blended.
Spoon into a shallow baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Combine flour and remaining one fourth of the brown sugar substitute; cut in 1 tablespoon margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over potatoes and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: banana-peanut ice cream
directions: Chill evaporated milk.
Mash bananas and set aside.
Whip chilled milk until it forms standing peaks.
Fold in mashed bananas and chopped peanuts.
Place in freezer.
After 30 minutes, remove from freezer and whip again.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart pan and return to freezer until firm.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook onions, bell peppers, garlic and celery in oleo until tender.
Add soups, parsley, onion tops, seafood and salt.
Simmer in rice.
Pour into large casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Can mix and refrigerate or freeze until ready to bake and serve.

title: rhubarb sauce deluxe
directions: Make syrup of sugar and water.
Boil together a few minutes. Add rhubarb to syrup when it starts boiling in center.
Watch closely and let boil just one minute.
Now here is the trick that makes ordinary rhubarb sauce a deluxe sauce.
Pour into a bowl or pan with a tight cover. Leave tightly covered until cold and you will find a sauce very different from any you have ever eaten.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut peeled potatoes into quarters or wedges.
Combine flour and cheese in plastic bag.
Moisten potatoes with water.
Shake in bag, a few at a time.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put potatoes in pan in one layer.
After 1/2 hour, turn the potatoes. Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: orange cake
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar to juice of 1 orange; mix well and let stand.
Soak raisins.
Add orange rind; put this mixture through food chopper or food processor.
Mix shortening, rest of sugar, eggs, sour milk (add 1 tablespoon vinegar to sweet milk), flour, baking soda, vanilla and the chopped raisins.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in a fluted or tube pan.
Pour juice and sugar over cake while hot.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks, milk, water, butter and vanilla.
Cook on medium high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Crumble vanilla wafers onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add sliced bananas on top of wafers.
Pour pudding mixture on top of bananas.
Beat egg whites until fluffy. Add 1/2 cup sugar until thick.
Pour on top of pudding.
Cook in oven at 350° until light brown on top.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
When cool enough to work with, scoop out potato centers.
Mash potatoes and save potato shells.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Leave 3 tablespoons of bacon fat in pan.
Add onions to bacon fat and cook until clear.
Drain off all fat.
Mix together potatoes, crumbled bacon, onion, cheeses, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stuff into potato shells.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Put ingredients in layers.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat; simmer 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, soup, water, soy sauce, onion and celery.
Place 1/2 fried noodles on bottom of casserole pan; add tuna mixture.
Top with balance of noodles.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup, water and canned chicken in pan on stove.
Cook on low heat until ingredients are well mixed. Pour mixture into baking pan.
Open cans of biscuits; arrange on top of mixture with edges of biscuits touching each other.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are light brown.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into a large bowl, measure 1/2 cup sugar and remaining ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well blended, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.

title: enchilada lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add seasoning mix and 1/3 jar picante sauce.
Grate Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheeses.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer tortillas, meat mixture, grated cheeses and picante sauce.
Top with cheeses and garnish with sliced olives and chopped bell pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Place in a 9 inch x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° covered for 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator nut cookies
directions: Cream the fat and sugar.
Add the egg and vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Add the nuts and combine with the first mixture.
Stir until blended.
Chill and then form into a roll of the desired size.
Roll in wax paper and chill thoroughly.

title: crock-pot chilli
directions: Brown beef until turns slightly brown. (It's better to leave it a little chunky.)
Put in crock-pot along with other ingredients in order listed. Stir once. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: cora's cherry pudding
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk, baking powder, salt and flour.
Put in greased 8-inch casserole.
Put cherries on top of batter; dot with margarine and add 1 cup sugar.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cherries will to to bottom and form a sauce.
(I usually double this and put in 9 x 13 pan.)
Serve with ice cream.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 2 minutes after each.
Add extract, buttermilk and flour.
Add coconut.
Stir well, then beat 2 1/2 minutes with mixer.
Bake 1 hour 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt butter in dish and coat bottom and sides of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk, sour cream and salt. Stir in scallions.
Pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
In mixing bowl, beat shortening and butter for 30 seconds; add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in oats and walnuts.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Form 1-inch balls. Dip tops of balls in additional sugar if desired.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ruthe's fruit salad
directions: Peel and dice apples and bananas.
Cut grapes in half.
Drain cherries and cut in half.
Add walnuts; add enough Miracle Whip to hold together.

title: cherry dessert bars
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar.
Blend butter or margarine into first mixture.
Spread into greased 10 x 10-inch pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: liver pate
directions: Cook chicken livers in boiling water.
Cool and put in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients, except Miracle Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in Miracle Whip.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of pie plate.
Pour chili on top of cream cheese.
Top with chopped chili peppers, then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and olives.

title: cholesterol free oatmeal-carrot cookies
directions: Beat applesauce and brown sugar until blended.
Add about 1/2 flour, the sugar, egg, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, cloves and vanilla.
Beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl. Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in oats, carrots and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart on cooking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: vegetable medley salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli and cauliflower.
Cut broccoli flowerets only and cauliflower into small pieces.
Mix dressing mix with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add bacon bits and cheese. Toss with vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: hello dollies
directions: Heat margarine in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine and pat into a crust.
Sprinkle in next 3 ingredients. Pour milk evenly over entire pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares while warm.
Yields 24.

title: doubly good yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl; mix 2 minutes on low speed of electric mixer and set aside.
Combine flour with remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix 3 minutes with a heavy-duty electric mixer at medium speed (5).
Add yeast mixture and mix 3 minutes at medium speed.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, about 3 hours or until the dough has doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
With lightly floured hands, shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in 3 greased 9-inch round pans.
Let dough rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, about 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake rolls at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: hot beef
directions: Put in oven for about 5 hours or until meat falls apart at 250°.
After done, mash with potato masher and serve in buns or over noodles.

title: pot-roast lamb(family recipe)
directions: Cut all fat from meat, and brown in Dutch oven with the butter. Turn meat to all sides to brown.
Remove from pot and saute cut up onions.
Remove onions and return lamb to pot.
Sprinkle the onions over the meat, add pepper, salt and caraway seed.
Cover and simmer until meat can be pierced with fork.
This will take about 2 hours on a low flame, or according to weight of meat.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Mix all ingredients.
Add broccoli and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes a large casserole.

title: white bean dip
directions: In a food processor, mince garlic.
Add beans; puree.
Add remaining ingredients; process until basil is finely chopped. Serve at room temperature or chilled with Crudites and pita chips.

title: cheese pate
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with plastic wrap and set aside. Combine first 3 ingredients in a small mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Spread into pie plate; sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve the yeast and sugar in warm water in a medium bowl. Mix in the Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Smooth into a ball on surface dusted with Bisquick.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch biscuits.
Put onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in a warm place 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 to 11 buns.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt in a large bowl. Beat well.
Mix soda and flour. Add to first mixture. Add apples and nuts. Stir until well blended.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hamburger cheese sandwich casserole
directions: Cut slices of bread into quarters.
Butter 3 slices on one side and put buttered sides down in a square baking dish.
Brown chopped vegetables; add hamburger and cook until red color is gone.
Add 2/3 of soup; do not dilute.
When mixed, pour mixture over bread in baking dish.
Top with remaining quarters of bread.
Beat egg and milk together; pour over sandwiches.
Spread remaining soup over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: tutti frutti ice cream
directions: Blend fruit in blender.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix all well.
Pour in 4-quart freezer.
Add milk to finish filling.

title: simple corn souffle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing, egg yolks, flour, sugar and pepper in a large bowl until smooth.
Stir in corn, cheese and onions.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into corn mixture.

title: texas millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramels and milk together over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add
nuts.
Drop
on
waxed paper and cool.
Melt chocolate
chips and paraffin together.
Dip cooled candy into chocolate and paraffin mixture.
Place on waxed paper.

title: snap doodle coffee cake
directions: Lightly
grease
bottom
of
an
oblong pan.
Mix eggs, sugar, evaporated
milk,	flour
and baking powder and put in pan.
Top with
butter, nuts and sprinkle brown sugar on top. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: sour cream cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries and pour into pie shell.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, flour, salt and sour cream thoroughly.
Pour over cherries.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° or until filling is set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: delicious cookie squares
directions: Mix fudge cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine and press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, nutmeg, and vanilla
together in baking dish. Break bread into mixture. Mix. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Drain. Stir together in a 9 x 13-inch pan the soups, sprouts and rice. Add meat mixture. Add soy sauce and mix well. Sprinkle chow mein noodles over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add sauce, beans and other ingredients, except egg and mashed potatoes.
Put meat mixture in a casserole.
Mix egg with mashed potatoes.
Place potato mixture in a ring around top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and then chop.
Mix Cheez Whiz with rice while rice is hot.
Add soup and broccoli.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: portabello and brie cups
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Spray 24 miniature muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray.
Brush mushrooms or wipe clean with damp cloth, finely chop.
In small skillet, combine mushrooms, margarine and garlic.
Cook over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes until mushrooms are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in green onions and mustard.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix flour mixture a little at a time into liquid.
Stir to mix well. Turn dough out on floured board.
Roll out and cut with a glass or a cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix 1 cup berries and 1/4 cup flour.
In medium bowl, stir together 1 3/4 cups flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/3 cup shortening, milk and egg; beat until smooth.
Stir in floured berries.
Pour into 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup blueberries over the top.

title: apple-raisin dressing
directions: Cook and stir celery and onion in margarine in 10-inch skillet until tender.
Stir in 1/3 of the bread cubes.
Pour into deep bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; toss.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or 3-quart casserole.
Cover and cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook until hot and slightly crisp (about 15 minutes longer).

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, oil and paprika.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Combine vegetables.
Pour liquid mixture over vegetables and marinate approximately 24 hours.
(May reserve liquid and use another time.)
Drain and serve salad.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Debone and cut turkey into chunks. Spread turkey over bottom of pie shell.
Add Veg-All vegetables and cream of chicken soup.
Pour 1/4 cup milk and broth over pie. Spread melted margarine over mixture.
Add top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is brown.

title: impossible chicken-vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.
Mix chicken, zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese.
Spoon evenly into pie plate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Prepare a 9 x 12 pan or 12-inch pie taker.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Combine softened margarine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onion and cheese.
Spread on the dinner rolls.
Put ham on top. Heat in oven for 10 minutes at 350° or microwave to heat.

title: italian beef
directions: Boil roast covered with water, seasoning and soup mix until tender.
Shred and add bouillon cubes.
Stir.
Simmer 15 minutes. Serve on Italian bread with peppers.

title: your own corned beef
directions: Combine spices, salt and water; boil 5 minutes and cool. Place beef and garlic in a crock.
Pour brine over the top and weight meat down to keep it submerged.
Tie cheesecloth over the top of crock and cover with a plate.
Pickle for 12 days in the fridge, rinse and use as any corned beef.

title: pumpkin nut roll
directions: Grease and flour 2 cookie sheets.
Beat the eggs for 5 minutes, gradually adding the remaining ingredients in order listed.
Spread mixture on cookie sheets and sprinkle finely chopped pecans on the rolls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Take a cloth and sprinkle with powdered sugar; dump cakes on this and roll up.
Cool 15 minutes.
Unroll cakes and spread icing on them and roll back up; wrap in aluminum foil.
Freeze and unthaw 20 minutes before serving.
Enjoy.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream sugar and crisco, add eggs and milk and mix well.
Stir in juice from the orange.
Add baking soda, powder, salt and flour and mix well.
Bake at 350 on a greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: roasted chinese chicken wings
directions: Put all ingredients except chicken into medium saucepan and heat over low heat until butter is melted and sugar dissolved. Arrange wings in single layer in large shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over wings and roast in 350° oven for 2 hours, turning wings after 1 hour.
Serve hot. Can be made and heated up in oven next day or in crock-pot.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown
hamburger
and put into stew pot.
In oil, saute onion, pepper
and
celery.
Add	vegetables to pot.
Add all other ingredients
to
the pot with the cabbage on top.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Trim fat from ham.
Heat fat in pan to render.
Remove rendered pieces and saute onion in drippings until soft.
Stir in potato slices, sauce mix, boiling water and milk.
Cut ham into bite size pieces and add to potatoes.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Lower heat and cover; simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: baked ham in coca-cola
directions: Cut Hostess ham in half long ways.
Mix in a bowl 2 cups Coca-Cola and 1 cup brown sugar.
Pour over ham and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn over every fifteen minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour and sugar; beat again. Blend in butter. Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: ricotta rice pie
directions: Rinse apples and dry them off.
Slice the apples and leave the skins on.
Put apples in a baking pan.
Put sugar, a little bit of flour and cinnamon on the apples.
Get a spoon and circle it around so it will all get mixed together.
Put in oven.

title: scrambled lasagne
directions: Mix Ricotta, milk, eggs, salt, pepper and some tomato sauce together.
Cook shells and drain; put in pan.
Add cheese mixture. Mix together.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with extra grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: brats my way
directions: Pierce the casing on the Brats with a fork a couple of times on each side. Toss in a large pot, add all ingredients, make sure the beer covers everything and bring to a slow boil. Boil at least an hour if not longer. (I like Polish sausage too, and make lots, they are better the next day!)

title: down home cube steak
directions: Dredge steaks in a combination of flour, black pepper and seasoning salt.
Brown in oil; place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Make gravy by adding mushroom soup mix, onion flakes, onion soup mix and black pepper to pan drippings.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add milk and heat until boiling.
Pour gravy over steaks. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve over hot mashed potatoes, cooked noodles or rice.

title: fanciful fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: gin's halfway chocolates
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12x8x2 inch baking dish.
Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Set aside.
Mix shortening with sugars until very light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, water, vanilla; mix well.
Thoroughly mix in flour mixture.
Pat into baking dish; top with chocolate bits.

title: bread in a bag
directions: Combine 1 cup of flour, yeast, dry milk and salt in a large Ziploc bag.
Shake to blend ingredients.
Add hot water and oil to dry ingredients.
Reseal and blend by working bag with fingers. Add whole wheat flour and mix thoroughly by working fingers over bag.
Add remaining flour to make a stiff dough; knead in bag with hands for 2 to 4 minutes.
Rest 10 minutes.
Take out of bag and form into a loaf.
Place in an oiled 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch pan.
Cover dough; let dough rise 20 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Remove fat and skin from chicken. Rub olive oil into chicken. Mix cinnamon, cumin, ginger, garlic, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle herb mixture onto skin side of chicken and allow to sit for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: spicy beef stew
directions: In pan, melt butter.
Coat beef with mixture of flour, salt, pepper, paprika and chili powder.
Cook in butter until browned. Pour into crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours, until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Melt margarine and add beaten eggs to sugar and flour, then add Karo, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and cook 30 to 35 more minutes.
Makes 3 small pies or 2 large pies.

title: nora's miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: jan's breakfast
directions: Cook and drain sausage. Butter the 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spread hash browns and onion in pan.
Put sausage on top of hash browns. Put mushrooms on the sausage. Beat the eggs and pour on top of the hash browns, sausage, etc.
Spread cheese on top of the eggs.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the best instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup hot water.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients 15 minutes, then add the rest of ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Blend flour and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, melted butter and coconut.
Pour into 1 unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tender beef brisket
directions: Place the brisket in a 3-quart slow cooker. In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Pour over brisket. Cover and cook on low for 6 hours or until tender. Remove the beef; set aside. Pour the sauce into a saucepan; cook, uncovered, over low heat for 13 to 15 minutes or until reduced and thickened, stirring occasionally. Slice the meat across the grain; serve with sauce. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: "pink stuff"
directions: Blend all together and chill.

title: new swing on fixing chicken(quick and easy)
directions: Fry, using 1 tablespoon butter or margarine and 1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce and chicken until done.
Serve with seasoned long grain and wild rice and tossed salad.
Whole meal takes less than 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in
skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients to beef and simmer for 2 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain, toss with egg, margarine & parmesan cheese.
Press in and up the sides of pie dish.
Spread cottage cheese over and into noodles.
In pan, cook beef, onion, and green peppers until meat is brown.
Drain; stir in spaghetti sauce and basil.
Heat on low for 10 minutes.
Spread over noodles and bake at 350 for 20 minutes.

title: cherry party salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: chinese salad dressing
directions: Mix well. Very good.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
In large saucepan, combine soup, milk and onion.
Add cream cheese, celery, carrot and Parmesan cheese.
Cook and stir until mixture is hot and cream cheese is melted.
Stir in chicken and broccoli.
Heat through.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole.

title: chocolate chip cheese loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend and divide into two loafs and garnish or roll in pecans.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix together and bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fritter-fry okra
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add mixture of eggs and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add okra and stir until well coated.
Spoon into hot fat and fry.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil carrots for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange in greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Combine oleo and cheese.
(I put oleo and Velveeta in measuring cup and melt on Medium in microwave.)
Pour over carrots.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: three cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Let cheese mixture stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with unsalted crackers, sliced apples or sliced pears

title: pickled eggs
directions: Slowly blend all ingredients except eggs.
Simmer 10 minutes, cool.
Then pour over eggs.
Place in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: quesadillas
directions: Take a taco shell, spread with butter on 1/2.
Cover 1/2 with cheese, onion and peppers, if you desire.
Zap on High in microwave for 1 minute or fry on grill until cheese is melted.
Fold in half and cut in fourths.
Serve immediately. Great served before a meal.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Measure Rice Krispies and set aside.
Measure and stir together in 6-quart boiler, the sugar and Karo. Stir and place over low heat, stirring constantly, until good boil.
(Do not overcook.)
Remove from fire.
Add peanut butter and margarine. Return to low heat and stir vigorously until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stew chicken and remove meat from bone.
Place a layer of tortilla chips on bottom of large casserole.
Pour broth over chips.
Spread pieces of chicken, followed by onion.
Repeat, layering ingredients again.
Sprinkle cheese over this.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and add tomato sauce. Stir in spaghetti sauce mix and let simmer while lasagna noodles are cooking. Drain noodles. Grease 9 x 13-inch dish. Put just enough sauce in bottom of pan to cover. Put a layer of noodles, layer of meat sauce and layer of cheeses. Repeat until all is used, ending with cheeses on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Serve hot. Sprinkle more Parmesan as desired on each serving. Add a salad and French rolls for a great meal.

title: parmesan wings
directions: Thaw wings.
Melt margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Dip wings in melted margarine, then into bread crumb/cheese mixture to coat.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, spread 1 box of stuffing and seasoning.
Spread vegetables over stuffing.
Next, spread chicken.
Mix milk and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Top with other box of stuffing and seasoning.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: pineapple-cream cheese dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and save 1 cup juice (add water to make 1 cup if needed).
Heat juice in microwave and add lemon juice; let cool.
Stir pineapple and cream cheese together and add Cool Whip. Fold cooled jello mixture into cream cheese mixture and chill several hours.

title: grilled turkey tenderloin
directions: Marinate turkey several hours in ingredients listed.
Grill turkey 8 to 10 minutes per side.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream cheese, margarine, sugar and powdered sugar.
Beat together in mixer.
In another bowl mix remaining ingredients. Pour in with the other ingredients and toss.
Pour in 2 graham cracker shells.
Decorate with nuts and cherries.
Cool 6 hours.

title: egg bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Oil a 1 1/2-quart fish mold.
In a large bowl, sprinkle gelatine over 1/4 cup of water and let stand until softened.
Add chicken stock and stir until dissolved.
Stir in dill and let cool for 10 minutes.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, green onions, paprika and salt.
Whisk well and refrigerate 20 to 30 minutes until it starts to thicken.
Add salmon; mix well and taste for seasoning.

title: microwave vidalia onions
directions: Cut out some of center of onion and add one pad of margarine to center.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes until done.
They are sweet and delicious.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix well in order given and pour into 8 x 10 x 2 inch dish and refrigerate until well chilled before serving.
Serves 10 - 12.

title: beef stew-oven baked
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in covered casserole. Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Stir after 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cold water. Add boiling water and stir over medium heat 10 to 12 minutes until thick. Take off heat and add small amount to beaten egg yolks. Then add back to mixture and add lemon juice; cook 2 minutes. Add butter and grated zest. Cool and pour into baked shell. Make meringue and put on top. Bake until brown at 325°.

title: good pork ribs
directions: Mix ingredients together and brush ribs.
Cook slow. If not enough, double the amount.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Prick several times with a fork.
Place potatoes 1-inch apart on a microwave-safe rack or paper towels. Microwave at High 10 minutes, turning and rearranging once.
Let cool to touch.
Cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on baking sheet coated with cooking spray and sprinkle with butter flavored sprinkles.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until crisp. Yields 4 servings (204 calories, 0% from fat).

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers, tomatoes, and onions as desired.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Toss oil over oysters.
Combine Hidden Valley (can use low-fat Hidden Valley), dill seed, garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Toss with oiled crackers until evenly coated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.
Good with graham cracker or oreo cookie crust.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine with mixer until dough holds together.
Stir in nuts.
Press half of mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chips over crust.
Pour caramels over chips, spreading evenly.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over caramel mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes longer.

title: nut bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 300° in ungreased cake pan.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream margarine.
Mix flour and confectioners sugar; add to margarine and mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pinch off dough and make into very small balls.
Bake at 325° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out as soon as they turn slightly brown. As soon as they come out of the oven, put them in a brown bag with about 2 cups sifted confectioners sugar.
Shake bag.
Take sand tarts out of bag; arrange on platter.

title: portland fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place crushed cereal in a plastic bag. Add chicken, one piece at a time, and shake to coat.
Place on nonstick baking sheet and sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix and cool or set and serve with Cool Whip.

title: russian pitter
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tomato herb soup
directions: Heat olive oil in large, heavy soup pot over medium heat and saute onions until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes more.
Raise heat to high and add garlic, bay leaf, thyme, marjoram, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and cook for 15 minutes.
Puree soup, 2 cups at a time, in blender.
Return soup to pot and reheat soup to boil over high heat.
Place two slices of toasted bread in each serving bowl. Ladle soup over bread and top with cheese.

title: rice brittle
directions: Cook water, sugar, cream of tartar, vinegar and butter.
Boil to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and rice. Stir until all the grains are coated.
Pour into buttered pan. Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a covered dish.

title: steak fajitas
directions: Brown steak with peppers and onions.
Add 57 sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Simmer until meat is soft, then place on tortilla and add optionals.

title: ice cream wafers
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well. Combine flour and salt; stir into creamed mixture. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets. Gently press a pecan half into the center of each cookie. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 1 minute. Carefully remove to wire racks to cool completely. Store in airtight container up to 1 week. These crispy, lemony cookies will keep in the freezer for months.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all the ingredients for sauce.
Slice the onion into circles and add to sauce.
Mix in cooked carrots.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in next 5 ingredients, then nuts. Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Set oven temperature control at 350°.
Continue baking 30 to 35 minutes.
(Filling should be slightly less set in center than around edges.)

title: apple cheese dessert
directions: Spread the apples in a pie pan or shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix cinnamon, flour, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in butter; stir in cheese.
Spread this mixture over the apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender, about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 30 minutes, covered, at 400° in a 2 1/2-quart dish or Dutch oven.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark, stir other ingredients in and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
May be frozen.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Mix crushed Butterfingers and Cool Whip together.
Add to crust.
Freeze and eat.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Prepare noodles according to package, then blot each with a paper towel to remove excess moisture.
Section sausage into 6 pieces.
Split sausage sections lengthwise almost all the way through and fill with a slice of cheese.
Wrap each stuffed sausage section in a noodle, secure with a toothpick and place in a square baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine eggs, onion, soup, Cheddar cheese and mayo.
Cook broccoli.
Mix dressing and margarine together.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Mix in a jar and shake well.
Pour over salad and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: spicy potatoes
directions: Add oil and spices to a hot frying pan.
Blend together.
Add potatoes to hot oil and spices.
Cook until tender.
All spices will cling to each potato cube.
Enjoy!

title: egg bake
directions: Grease 7 x 11-inch pan.
Place 7 slices bread on bottom.
Top with bacon and then cheese.
Place 7 slices bread over this.
Beat mustard, eggs and milk together and pour on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour in saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Whip cream and fold in sliced bananas, pecans and 3/4 of coconut.
Fold whipped cream mixture into cooled pineapple mixture.
Pour into pie shells; sprinkle remaining coconut on top. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with red and green maraschino cherries.

title: macaroni-tomato cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions minus 2 minutes.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Pour into large mixing bowl.

title: chocolate-tipped butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Shape dough into 2 1/2 x 1/2-inch sticks.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten 3/4 of each cookie lengthwise with tines of fork to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: coconut toast
directions: Cream
together margarine, sugar and egg.
Add coconut; spread on bread and bake at 350° until evenly browned.

title: date nut bread
directions: Add baking soda to nuts and dates, then boiling water; next sugar and butter.
Drop in egg; stir well.
Add vanilla and flour. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: island dreams(4 dozen cookies)
directions: Toast coconut and almonds on a cookie sheet at 350° for 4 to 6 minutes.
Cream butter and white and brown sugars until light.
Add vanilla and coconut extracts.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cornstarch.
Stir into butter mixture, using a spoon rather than a mixer.
Add coconut and almonds.

title: latkes or potato pancakes
directions: Wash, peel and grate potatoes (raw).
Grate onion and add to potatoes.
Beat eggs well.
Add to potato mixture.
Add salt and flour.
Mix well.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix together and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve on hot dogs.

title: speedy baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion yellow. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in a 350° oven until beans are bubbly.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix beans and taco seasoning.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Then layer next 5 items. Mash avocado with fork; mix in mayo and lemon juice.
Spread in pan.
Next, put diced tomato; top with cheese.
Chill for at least 6 hours.
Serve with traditional Tostitos or other dip chips. Makes 20 to 30 servings.

title: milk punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 1 gallon freezer container. Place in freezer at least overnight.
Remove 1 hour before serving; in summer, 1/2 hour.
Keeps several weeks in freezer. Serves 32 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large pot lightly brown pieces of chicken in olive oil. Add all other ingredients; simmer (covered) until tender (about 1 1/2 hours) or may bake in a 350° oven about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir chicken 2 to 3 times during cooking time.
Serves 6.

title: gazpacho dip
directions: Chill overnight!
Makes a great salsa; wonderfully easy for company.

title: kay's broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg lightly in 1 cup measuring cup.
Then fill rest of cup with milk.
Add to dry ingredients and heat a little.
Let rise for 5 minutes.
Drop batter by tablespoons in boiling water or stew.
Cover and let boil for 20 minutes.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add eggs, flour and baking powder.
Pour half in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over mixture; spread can of cherry pie filling.
Pour rest of mixture over pie filling.
Top with more sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Can also use lemon, blueberry or apple pie filling in place of the cherry.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill for an hour.
Shape into bite-size balls.
For later use, freeze on a cookie sheet, then place in plastic bags.
To heat, place on cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 350° (longer if frozen).

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cut cake in very thin slices.
Place layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan, cutting same number of slices for second layer. Soften cream cheese; add sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla until well blended.
Pour half over cake slices.
Add second cake layer. Spoon rest of cheese mixture over cake slices, covering completely.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill for 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water on chocolate, stirring until melted; cool.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat in chocolate mixture and vanilla on low speed.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until batter is smooth. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour into pan. Bake about 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Spread Caramel Topping over hot cake; sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake about 20 minutes longer or until chocolate chips melt.
Cool before serving.

title: paint brush cookies
directions: Have an adult heat the oven to 375°.
Slice the cookie roll into 1/4-inch slices.
Put them on a cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Mix egg yolk and water, then divide into 4 small dishes. Mix one drop of food coloring in each dish.
Make each dish a different color.
Use a clean paint brush to paint designs on the cookies.
Bake in the oven 8 to 10 minutes.
(Make sure an adult is helping you.)

title: crab dip
directions: Heat cream cheese in microwave until soft. Mix remaining ingredients with cream cheese. This is a good dip served hot or cold. If you like it less spicy, delete the jalapenos.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until dry.
Add 1 quart milk until creamy.
Add sugar and raisins.
Beat eggs with fork and add to mixture.
Stir in 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Chill and serve.

title: microwave chocolate pudding
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-proof dish, stir together milk, cocoa, salt, sugar and cornstarch until cornstarch dissolves.
Cook on High (100%) power for 2 minutes.
Stop, take mixture out and whip with wire whip.
Return to microwave and use wire whip to beat mixture.
Return to microwave for 2 additional minutes on High. Remove from microwave, using wire whip, beat in margarine, vanilla extract and packets of sweetener.
Pour into individual serving dishes.
Refrigerate.
Yield:
5 (1/2 cup) servings.
Contains 125 calories per serving.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 muffins.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook meat until it loses red color.
Add remaining ingredients except peas.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 50 minutes.
Add peas; cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot with garlic bread.
This freezes well.
Just heat and serve.

title: peach cake or cookie dough
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and add beaten egg and vanilla.
Mix with remaining ingredients. If dry, add a few tablespoons of water so dough is pliable enough to press into a greased 9 x 1-inch cake pan.
Top with unpeeled peaches or plums cut into wedges or strawberries or blueberries.
Dot fruit with butter and sprinkle it with sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Squeeze lemon juice over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is lightly browned.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill after mixing at least 1 hour. Bake at 375° about 9 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat egg slightly and mix with remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pack firmly in greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch microproof loaf pan. Cover with waxed paper and cook on 70 (Roast) for 25 to 30 minutes, or until center of loaf is done.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before slicing.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into a greased muffin tin.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 large or 9 small rolls.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Drain.
Put on jelly roll pan. Pour beaten eggs over spaghetti.
Pour Ragu sauce over spaghetti. Put slice pepperoni all over sauce, as much as you like.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese turns golden brown.
May use any topping you like.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: You need 3 bowls (1 large and 2 small).
In first small bowl, put butter and boiling water.
Stir until melted.
In second small bowl, put 1/2 cup warm water and yeast.
In large bowl, put eggs, sugar, salt and milk.
Put all mixtures in large bowl, stirring, and add flour.
Knead into loaf.
Cover; put in refrigerator overnight or until needed.
About 3 hours before dinner, shape into rolls; let rise and bake at 350° until lightly browned. (I've been making these for 30 years and they never fail.)

title: coated pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add other ingredients.
Dip pecans in this, one at a time.
Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake 30 minutes at 225°, then turn oven off and let stay for 30 minutes more.
It takes a good while to dip the pecans, so don't turn your oven on until you get them on the sheet.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend ingredients and pour into a heated 9-inch graham cracker shell. Bake at 325° for 7 to 9 minutes. CHILL, SERVE AND ENJOY!

title: bran cereal muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine cereal and milk in bowl and let stand about 3 minutes; stir well.
Add egg and oil; blend well.
Add flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten flour (batter will be thick).
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling each 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cool about 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: cream of tomato soup(4 servings)
directions: In saucepan, cook onions in butter with salt until onions are soft and translucent.
Add herbs, pepper and saute a few minutes more.
Add tomatoes, sherry and honey.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut cream cheese into small cubes and add to hot soup. Stir and cook until smooth.
Serve garnished with chopped flat leafed parsley.

title: country style steak
directions: Flour steak; salt and pepper.
Fry good and brown.
Remove from pan.
Pour off some grease, leaving about 2 tablespoons grease.
Add about 3 to 4 tablespoons flour; mix and brown.
Add hot water; stir and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat.
Add steak; simmer for about 5 hours.
Keep checking to see if you need to add water.

title: kool-aid fun(fun, clean, good-smelling play doh!)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix liquids together and pour into dry.
Stir until it forms a ball.

title: sausage corn bread
directions: Cook sausage, drain and crumble.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix in order given in a large bowl, then press mixture into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, set aside.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well margarine and sugar and add eggs (one at a time), flour, flavoring and cocoa.
Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Batter will rise up, then fall down.
I bake them in four round cake pans, two pans at a time, unless your oven is wide enough to bake all 4 on 1 rack.
Makes 48 big squares and corners. To keep fresh, they are best to freeze and take out as you want them.

title: steak and rice casserole
directions: In a crock-pot, put prepared peppers, celery, soups and milk over vegetables and steak.
Cook on low for 6 hours.
Add rice and cook on high for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain off fat.
Put in crock-pot with all ingredients.
When cheese and ingredients are melted together, serve with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion in fat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour. Add meatballs to sauce for the last 15 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together.
Roll into small balls.
Stick with toothpicks. Freeze for a few minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans and parsley.
Roll into a ball.
Mix pecans and parsley and roll cheese in mixture. Chill and serve.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute first three ingredients together in 1 tablespoon oil. Cook all ingredients together.
Serve in soup bowls and top with Parmesan cheese.
May add small amount of spaghetti if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 4 minutes in salted water.
Drain and place in casserole.
Cover with sliced water chestnuts.
Sprinkle grated cheese over chestnuts.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over cheese. Make holes with fork so soup spreads through mixture.
Bake at 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Put onion rings on top and brown.

title: easy chili
directions: Saute onions in margarine. Add other ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Layer rolls, then remaining ingredients, then more rolls. Glaze while hot.

title: brown bag caramel corn
directions: Combine everything, except soda and popcorn and put in 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish.
Put in microwave and bring to a boil, then cook on full power for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda (mixture will foam up).
Put the popped corn in a brown grocery bag and pour syrup over the corn.
Close bag and shake. Cook in bag on High in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes if necessary (corn should not be sticky).
Pour into a pan and cool.

title: fat men cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt until thick and light.
Add cream and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Cut dough into diamond shapes and fry in hot shortening (375°).
While warm, sprinkle cookies with granulated sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken dinner casserole
directions: Rinse frozen peas and carrots under running cold water to separate; drain.
Mix peas and carrots, onions, mushrooms (with liquid), soup and chicken in ungreased 2-quart casserole or 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with chips.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until hot and bubbly, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and up sides of pan about an inch.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar thoroughly and pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
Looks like it has fallen. Rich.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Let all ingredients except flour come to boil; remove from the fire.
Cool, then stir in flour.
Let bake 1 1/4 hours in a slow oven (350°).

title: jalapeno pepper pie(appetizer)
directions: Slice peppers into thin strips.
Scatter over bottom of glass pie plate.
Slice olives and scatter between peppers.
Pile grated cheese on top.
Pour beaten eggs over all.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Cheese should be melted and set, but not brown.
Allow to cool to warm.
Cut into cubes. Serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: crepes
directions: Beat ingredients with a rotary mixer until smooth.
Pour a scant 1/4 of a cup into a buttered skillet; brown and turn.
Fill with filling of choice or with berries or fruit and top with powdered sugar, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: pork chops or breast of chicken
directions: Brown meat; set aside.
Butter baking dish; pour in rice, green pepper, celery and mushrooms over meat.
Take onion soup mix and sprinkle 1 teaspoon on each piece of meat.
Sprinkle rest in dish.
Add water and mushroom juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered. Serves 4.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Beat egg, oil and sugar together.
Add molasses and stir.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls, dip in sugar and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Should be cracked on top.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cook peas for 1 minute.
Drain.
In large bowl layer lettuce, celery, green pepper and peas.
Spread mayonnaise evenly on top. Sprinkle with cheese, then bacon.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hrs. Toss at serving time.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spicy prune cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over oats and prunes, stirring to combine; cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat margarine until creamy; gradually add sugars, beating until fluffy.
Stir in egg.
Add oats and prune mixture, mixing well. Pour batter into greased and floured 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: cherry-berries in a cloud
directions: Mix together pie filling, strawberries and lemon juice. Set into the refrigerator.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight and serve with Bugles.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put half of strawberry mixture into 12 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm; spread evenly over top with sour cream.
Spoon rest of Jell-O mixture and refrigerate.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix meat, eggs, bread crumbs and onion soup.
Mix together, make meatballs and place on cookie sheet.
Bake until meat is no longer red.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil all the ingredients except the popped corn to 270° crack stage.
Use vanilla to keep hands from sticking. Also flavors the popcorn balls.

title: party punch
directions: You can put this in plastic jugs and freeze. Take out 2 to 3 hours before and you will have a slush.

title: chicken modiga
directions: Melt 1/4 C. butter in sauce pan, set aside.
Cut remaining 1/2 C. butter in half.
Put butter and flour in mixing bowl.
Mash with fork to make creamy mixture.
Set aside.
Cut each chicken breast in half, to make 4 pieces of chicken.
Wash chicken, drain off excess water.
Dredge chicken in bread crumbs.
Using pastry brush, brush reserved melted butter on chicken to moisten bread crumbs.

title: mexican beans and franks
directions: In saucepan, brown frankfurters and cook green pepper with chili powder in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat; stir occasionally.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring water, sugar and pie filling to a boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add Jell-O. Stir until well dissolved. Add the pineapple juice. Stir well. Add Coke and nuts. Stir well and pour into a large bowl or make 2 small ones. Refrigerate.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place half of onions in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with half of crackers and half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir pudding mix into milk in medium saucepan.
Add egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Arrange layer of cookies on bottom and up sides of 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Add one layer of banana slices; top with 1/3 pudding.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding.
Beat egg whites and salt in medium bowl with electric mixer on high speed until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spoon lightly onto pudding, sealing edges well.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned.
Serve warm or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix cheese, onion, soup and sour cream in a bowl; add salt and pepper.
Put hash browns in glass dish (9 x 13-inches).
Pour all ingredients over the top, then the melted butter and sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy spinach party loaf
directions: Cut slice from top of bread; remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into bite sized pieces; reserve.
Brush insides of shell with 3 tablespoons margarine, melted.
Place on cookie sheet with reserved bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Saute peppers, celery and onions in remaining margarine until tender.
Add process cheese spread; stir over low heat until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Pour into bread shell; serve with reserved bread, top slice and assorted vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In a large bowl mix the sugar and flour together; then add the pineapple and cheese.
Mix by a folding motion.
Transfer into an 8 x 8 inch casserole that has been sprayed with vegetable oil. Melt the butter in a pan; add pineapple juice and stir in the crackers.
Then spread this over the casserole
Bake at 350° preheated oven for 24 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Saute chopped garlic and onion in butter until tender.
Add wine; turn heat to simmer.
Add baby clams with juice, plus 2 bottles clam juice.
Add spices.
Stir frequently.
Cook macaroni; drain and place in a bowl.
Either spoon onto macaroni to serve individually or pour sauce over all macaroni and then serve.

title: pickle beans
directions: Wash green beans; snap.
Use clean sterile jars.
(Full beans are best.)
Add 1 teaspoon salt to each quart jar.
Cook beans with just enough water to cover beans, using cold water.
Cook beans just until tender.
Don't overcook.
Drain off water.
Cool beans.

title: chocolate (sauerkraut) cake
directions: Thoroughly cream the margarine with the sugar.
