Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately with water to egg mixture. Stir in kraut.
Turn into two greased and floured 9-inch round pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Spoon the first 3 ingredients over the chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.
Delicious.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix and simmer as long as you want to serve.

title: fruit topping surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: cherry dream salad
directions: Combine fruit juices, sugar, lemon juice and eggs. Stir and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and cool. Fold in sour cream. Add marshmallows and remaining ingredients (cherries, oranges, pineapple chunks, coconut and nuts).
Let mixture stand in the refrigerator for about 24 hours.

title: cool whip chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks in milk.
Melt chocolate in microwave; add to first mixture.
Cook on medium heat in saucepan until thick.
Add vanilla; stir in butter. Pour into baked shells.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip; keep in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
When golden brown, add brown sugar.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the boiling water.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown meat and drain; reserve fat in skillet.
Remove meat to a 2-quart baking dish.
Saute onion in fat.
Drain off fat and mix onion with meat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until celery is tender.
Cover the dish the last half hour of baking.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Debone chicken and cut into strips.
Marinate in sauce overnight.
Grill.

title: strawberry nut spread
directions: Mix well and spread on rye or whole grain bread.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove from pans.
After complete cooling, sprinkle with remaining cup of nuts.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Add soups and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Fold in broccoli and rice and add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: easy tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello with scant cup of boiling water.
Add contents of the can.
Pour in mold and let set in refrigerator.
Makes nice salad slices if molded in bread pan.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into mold and allow to set in refrigerator.

title: caramel flan
directions: In a heavy saucepan over medium-low heat, cook and stir sugar until melted and golden, about 15 minutes. Quickly pour into an ungreased 2-quart round baking dish, tilting to coat the bottom. Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: dang good pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour filling into pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until set and brown.

title: honey chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces on foil-lined pan.
Put 1 teaspoon of sauce on each piece.
Cover with foil.
Bake in oven or grill on low for 45 minutes.
Turn often.
Remove from foil and grill. Refill cup with barbecue sauce and spoon over chicken.
Turn chicken often until done to suit your taste.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
While cake is still warm, poke holes in cake all over.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake.
After cake cools, frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with Heath candy bars.

title: cajun bean soup
directions: Place ham bone in enough water to cover in a large stock pot. Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer for 6 to 8 hours.
Add green onions, parsley and sausage 1 hour before serving.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon. Boil until dissolved.
Gradually add noodles and salt.
Boil 3 minutes, uncovered.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes until broccoli is tender.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Chop onion.
Crush crackers.
Mix all ingredients well.
Make into patties.
Fry or broil in oven.

title: baked pork chops
directions: A quick and easy, as well as tasty way to have pork chops. Simply use crock-pot, placing cream of mushroom soup on bottom (undiluted) of pot, then put chops, layering them with the soup. Cook with crock-pot on high for at least 4 hours.
Delicious!
It is best to rotate the chops, turning them over at least once.

title: easy peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Take off stove and add peanut butter.
Beat until the gloss is gone.
Then pour into a buttered pan and let cool.

title: orange treat cake
directions: Mix 3 ounces of juice in cake mix.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, substituting 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip for the oil or butter.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch layer pans about 30 minutes.
Cool in pans on racks 15 minutes, remove from pans and cool completely.
Beat cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining Cool Whip and juice.
Frost cake. Refrigerate cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; cool.
Add onion.
Mix with mayonnaise, salt, pepper, soup, eggs and half of cheese.
Bake at 350° until thickened.
Sprinkle remaining cheese (I use a little more than 1/2 cup) on top for last 5 minutes. Bake until top is brown.

title: blueberry cream muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs thoroughly and gradually add sugar.
Slowly pour in oil; add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with the sour cream to the egg mixture. Gently fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins or cupcake liners.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: quick sugar cookie sticks
directions: Heat oven to 375.
Mix sugar, the butter, vanilla, almond extract and egg in large bowl with spoon.
Stir in flour baking powder and salt.
Divide dough into halves.
Shape 1 half into 2 strips, 15 x 3 inches, 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until golden, approximately 7 to 9 minutes; cool 2 minutes.
Cut crosswise into 1-inch slices; drizzle with glaze.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Store loosely covered. Makes about five dozen cookies.

title: strawberry cheesecake trifle
directions: Mix vanilla and almond extract; set aside.
In a small, deep bowl, whip the cream, vanilla and sugar.
Fold whipped cream into cream cheese mixture.
Add cake pieces; set aside.
Combine strawberries, sugar and almond extract.

title: microwave irish coffee
directions: Use a biscuit cutter and cut the center out of a slice of buttered bread.
Both sides should be buttered.
Place in a skillet over medium heat.
Place an egg in the hole.
Cook for about one minute and turn.
Place a slice of any type of cheese on the cooked side and continue to cook for about another minute.

title: paella
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring 3 1/2 cups of water to a boil. Add contents of the box and tablespoon of Goya olive oil, corn oil or butter. Stir. Boil for 1 minute; cover tightly and reduce heat to low. Cook for 25 minutes or until water is absorbed. Five minutes before it is done, add your favorite seafood, such as shrimp, mussels, clams or whatever else you want; cook until fish is cooked.

title: drop ginger cookies
directions: Cream egg, butter, sugar and molasses.
Add dry ingredients. Stir in raisins.
Drop teaspoon-sized dough on greased tin.
Bake at 350° for
7 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Put yeast in water and set aside. Add shortening and sugar to buttermilk.
Beat eggs; add to yeast, then combine into milk mixture.
Make a well in flour and add ingredients.
Cover with cloth and allow to rise to top of bowl.
Put in refrigerator to chill. Roll out like biscuits and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding enough Miracle Whip to make right consistency.
Best if eaten immediately.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Add the gelatine.
Stir to combine.
Fold in the drained shrimp. Pour into a jello mold and refrigerate until dip is set.
Serve with crackers.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook down until thick like honey; seal in sterile jars.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves lengthwise.
Remove yolks with fork.
Smash yolks.
Add rest of ingredients; beat until well mixed.
Fill egg whites with mixture.
Garnish tops with dash of paprika, chopped parsley or chopped chives.

title: tea cakes
directions: Place flour in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, lard, eggs and vanilla.
Mix by hand until all flour is absorbed.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead until dough is stiff (may have to add flour).
Roll thin and cut desired size.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: super lazy dinner
directions: In the morning before leaving for work, put the ribs and the bottle of barbecue sauce in crock-pot.
Turn it on the low setting.
Eat when you get home from work!

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Put into greased casserole.
Cover with the crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except pecans.
Put in freezer until firm.
Roll in ball, then roll in chopped pecans.
Serve on Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Cut about 1/2 inch off top of cake.
Pinch out bite-size pieces, leaving 1/2 inch on sides.
Mix strawberries and some of whipped topping and unmixed Jell-O together.
Layer mixture, unmixed Jell-O and bite-size pieces in cake.
Put top back on and ice with whipped topping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, bacon and onion in bowl; mix well. Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl. Add to broccoli mixture; mix well. Chill for 2 hours or longer. YIELD: 8 servings.

title: french omelet
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Beat in milk or cream and seasoning. Pour into fat in skillet over low heat.
Cook slowly, keeping heat low.
As under surface becomes set, start lifting it slightly with spatula to let uncooked portion flow underneath and cook.
To add herbs, cheese or meat, sprinkle 1/2 tablespoon per egg over top of eggs.
As soon as all of the mixture seems set, fold and roll it. Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken fajita
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix lemon juice, oil, seasoning, oregano and peppers and marinate chicken for several hours.
Stir-fry chicken until cooked.
Add cut up pepper, onion, mushrooms and tomatoes and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Serve with hot tortillas and Spanish rice.
Grate cheese and lettuce for garnish.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: In a skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook rice and onion until rice is lightly browned.
Stir constantly.
Stir in broth.
Heat to boiling.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Cover; cook 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and rice is tender, stirring rice mixture occasionally.
Garnish chicken with lemon slice with paprika, if desired.

title: peanut butter gems
directions: Mix all together but the chocolate chips and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread melted chocolate chips on top.
Chill and cut into squares.
Don't chill too long!

title: chicken livers
directions: Melt margarine.
Cook celery, onion and chicken livers until tender.
Stir in cornstarch, adding 1 cup of water and remaining ingredients, except rice.
Heat 5 to 10 minutes. Serve over rice. (Beef livers may also be used in lieu of chicken livers.)

title: seasoning for pretzels
directions: Mix oil, lemon pepper, dill weed, garlic pepper, and Hidden Valley Ranch Dressing in a small mixing bowl.
Mix with pretzels in a large bowl.
Stir well, cover and let stand 24 hours.
Stir well.

title: fri chik broccoli divan
directions: Cut broccoli into pieces.
If frozen is used, cook and drain it.
Slice up Fri Chik and grate cheese and melt the butter.
In a 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole, arrange broccoli and put Fri Chik on top.
Combine soup and milk and pour over Fri Chik and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cooled cornbread and set aside.
Mix mayo, pickles and juice; set aside. Mix pepper, onion, tomatoes and bacon; set aside.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Heat until red hots melt.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: lemon-berry parfaits
directions: In 4 parfait glasses alternate layers of yogurt and raspberries.
Garnish with whipped cream and candied lemon slices, if desired.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat all ingredients to a boil.
Then let simmer.
Serves 4.

title: pink magic pie(rhubarb)
directions: Place rhubarb in pie shell.
Mix eggs, flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over rhubarb.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sticky cinnamon rolls
directions: In a small bowl, combine confectioners sugar and cream.
Divide evenly between two greased 9-inch square baking pans.
Sprinkle with pecans; set aside.
On a floured surface, roll each loaf of bread dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Brush with butter. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over butter.
Top with raisins, if desired.
Roll up from a long side.
Pinch seam to seal.
Cut each roll into 12 slices.
Place with cut side down in prepared pans.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from the refrigerator.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 2 hours. Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Uncover and bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: light ambrosia cake
directions: Bake
cake
mix
as
directed on package in 13 x 9-inch pan. While cake is Warm, sprinkle the cut up oranges over it. Mix pudding using skimmed milk as directed on package and pour over oranges.
Mix
coconut
into
Cool Whip and pour over the pudding. Keep refrigerated.

title: john's stew
directions: Add everything together and season to taste.
For the average family you can cut the recipe in half.

title: cheese stuffed shells
directions: Mix all ingredients but sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Stuff cooked shells with mixture.
Place shells in large flat baking dish that has a thin layer of spaghetti sauce on bottom.
Pour rest of sauce over.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: southern chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and arrange in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup, water, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in a small bowl; mix well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or just until heated through.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reserve 2 cups of dough for the icing.

title: ice cream-jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir well to dissolve. Quickly add and stir in completely the softened ice cream. (The jello needs to be hot to melt in the ice cream. The ice cream should be softened, but not melted before adding.) Mix in the remaining ingredients and refrigerate in a serving bowl until well set, overnight or several hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Set aside 1 1/2 tablespoons of tomato paste.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Mix 1 1/2 tablespoons tomato paste with water; smooth over top of loaf.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Blend
cream
cheese
and
salmon very well with liquid smoke. Form into ball (this will seem a little soft) and roll in
finely chopped fresh parsley and pecans.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Mix in with broccoli. Beat (or mix in blender) the eggs, cream and salt.
Spread cheese and broccoli evenly over bottom of pie shell.
Place pie pan on cookie sheet.
Pour cream mixture over broccoli.
Bake on lowest rack of oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of 11 1/2 x 17 1/2-inch pan with lid.
Spray with Pam first.
Arrange and pat together at seams to form a single piece.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; watch carefully (do not overbrown).
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing together.
After dough cools, spread with 1/2 of cream cheese mixture.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups.
Beat egg with fork. Stir in milk and oil.
Measure flour, blend dry ingredients and stir in just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy. Fill muffin cup 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm. Makes 12.

title: copenhagen brussels sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts.
Drain off liquid.
Mix Italian dressing, pimentos and mushrooms together and heat.
Pour over cooked Brussels sprouts.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble on top of Brussels sprouts.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: easy creamed cukes
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Add onion and green pepper, sugar and Miracle Whip.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and refrigerate a couple hours before serving.
Stir right before serving.
Makes its own juice.
Lasts for days in refrigerator.

title: supper a la king
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot butter, cook green pepper and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup and milk; blend well.
Stir in meat and pimento.
Cook 5 minutes more or until heated through.

title: strudel - cool dough
directions: Melt margarine.
Add to mixture consisting of:
warm milk, egg yolks and flour.
Mix together and divide dough in 6 portions. Chill for at least 3 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together until real fine.
Put apples in bottom of baking pan.
Sprinkle over top with the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg mixture.
Melt 1/3 cup butter and sprinkle over top.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top last.
(You can use any kind of fruit.)
Bake in oven at 350° or 375° for 35 minutes or until fruit is done.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon. Remove skin and bones. Place in bowl with cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke; beat with mixer at medium speed until smooth. Chill several hours. Combine parsley and pecans on waxed paper. Shape salmon mixture into ball and roll in nuts and parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: dill and lemon balm muffins
directions: Mix first three ingredients and add dill and lemon balm.
Add flour and sugar; mix.
Put into muffin tins and brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut in quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in bag, coating potatoes well with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in a layer in pan. Bake at 375° for one hour, turning once.
When brown, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients plus a dash of cinnamon, if desired.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon 3 inches apart onto aluminum foil-lined cookie sheets. Bake at 350°
for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are brown.
Cool completely before removing.
Yields about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: homemade "egg beaters"
directions: Blend until smooth.
Store in a jar in the refrigerator for up to 1 week or freeze.
One-fourth cup equals 1 whole egg.

title: hors d'oeuvres cheese dip(microwave oven)
directions: Place cheese spread cubes in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at 50% power for 3 to 6 minutes or until melted, stirring once.
Beat in beer and garlic with wire whip until smooth.
Microwave at High until heated, about 1 minute; garnish with pimiento and parsley.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Place beef in 2 qt. baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix, lemon-lime soda and tapioca over beef; stir until blended.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine beans with seasoning mix.
Spread bean mix in 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer the remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes on High in microwave oven.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook and stir pepper and onion in hot oil in saucepan until tender but

not browned. Add corn, salsa and broth; bring to a boil. Stir in rice; cover. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Add cheese; fluff with fork. This recipe may be halved or doubled. Makes 8 servings.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in kettle.
Place over low heat until sugar is dissolved or until fruit is clear.
Take off of heat. Add dry Jell-O.
Can or freeze.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water with chopped celery and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove cooked chicken from pot and debone it, cutting chicken into small pieces.
To broth add: chopped chicken, cheese, mushroom soup, peas, pimentos and noodles.
Cook mixture until noodles are soft, then pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until noodles are done and mixture is thick.

title: romaine lettuce salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and toss with Raspberry dressing. Serves 8-10.

title: quick and easy nutty chess cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan. Can spray with Pam. Mix cake mix, oleo and pecans and put in pan. Mix brown sugar and cream cheese. Place this on top of cake mix mixture. Put pecans on top of this. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: swiss potato soup(serves 8 cups)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in Dutch oven.
Remove bacon.
Saute onion in bacon fat.
Add potatoes, turnip and broth; simmer until done.
Puree mixture in blender.
Return puree to Dutch oven; heat to boiling.
If desired, stir in sour cream.

title: gop meatballs
directions: Combine all but the jelly and chile sauce together.
Form meatballs the size of a walnut and brown (skillet or oven).
Drain well.
Heat jelly and chile sauce and simmer over stove or in a crock-pot, stirring occasionally.
Add meatballs and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and oleo.
Add eggs; mix.
Add bananas, soda, salt, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, over low heat, cook butter, sugar and water until melted.
Add chocolate pieces and stir until partially melted.
Remove from heat and continue to stir until completely melted.
Pour into large mixer bowl and let stand 10 minutes to cool.

title: shirley's baked rhubarb
directions: Place rhubarb in greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and butter; spoon over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: vidalia casserole
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Saute onions until clear.
Layer onion and 2/3 of cheese in casserole dish.
Heat soup, milk and soy sauce together.
Pour over onions.
Top with French bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Push bread into liquid.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: 20 minute chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into egg then into crumb to coat.
Brown chicken on both sides in skillet over medium heat in 2 teaspoons margarine.
Add Prego sauce; reduce heat and simmer covered for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley and simmer covered for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: never fail chocolate mousse
directions: Using a blender, combine eggs, instant coffee, chocolate and liqueur.
Bring milk to a boil.
Pour hot milk into blender container with other ingredients; cover and mix on high speed for exactly 2 minutes.
Pour into a Pyrex dish and chill for at least 4 hours.
Serve topped with whipped cream if desired.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice and mustard until smooth.
Stir in the broccoli and pepper.
Set aside. Lightly break up the potato interior with a fork without breaking through the peel.
Top each potato half with the broccoli-cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve hot.

title: pickled black-eyed peas("texas caviar")
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into jar.
Refrigerate.
Remove garlic after 1 day.
May be kept up to two weeks in the refrigerator.

title: aunt hattie's refrigerator gingerbread muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and stir.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to molasses-sugar mix. Add soda, dissolved in hot water.
Add vanilla, raisins and pecans.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Batter can be kept in refrigerator several days.
Bake as needed.

title: cream cheese crab royal
directions: Place softened cream cheese on large serving plate.
Rinse canned crab meat.
Top cream cheese with meat and cocktail sauce, letting sauce run over sides.
Place variety of crackers around serving platter.
Decorate with parsley.
Serve cold.

title: snow cones
directions: Freeze orange juice (or any other juice) in ice cube trays. Pop frozen juice cubes into plastic bag to store.
Put 3 to 6 of these cubes at a time in a blender.
Turn blender on and off until cubes reach snowy consistency.
Pile into a paper cup to serve. Or blend the whole batch and store in freezer.
Kids can serve themselves.
Add a little water to make a slush.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole in preheated 350° oven. Stir in other ingredients. Cover tightly with foil. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to an
hour. Check. If watery or soupy, uncover and cook 5 minutes more. Serves 8.

title: baked fresh ham with sherry baste
directions: Remove rind from ham.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in a roaster pan, bone side down, and with a sharp knife, score the top in a diamond design.
This will help to sherry the meat.
Add the water and tent with heavy foil.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for approximately 4 hours or until the ham is tender and pulls away from the bone.
Every 30 minutes, baste the ham with sherry.
Save the brownings in the pan for gravy.

title: braised jerusalem artichokes
directions: In an 8 or 9-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic and saute until onion is lightly browned.

Add artichoke slices, salt and pepper and saute for 5 minutes; add wine and cook until almost all liquid has evaporated. Add water, cover and let simmer, stirring occasionally, until artichokes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with parsley.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: chicken ka boom
directions: (Warning: This will explode and cause a fire if baked in a domed roaster pan.
Don't ask me how I know!)

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and butter. Bake in 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pie crust(no cholesterol)
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Combine milk and syrup.
Add to flour all at once.
Mix and roll to fit 9-inch pie pan sprayed with Pam.
Cool before filling.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: In large pan, fry chicken and onion in cooking oil until well browned.
Add the rest of the ingredients except for the sour cream and cheese.
Simmer covered on low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: elby's strawberry pie
directions: Mix together real good until smooth, then add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Put on stove and bring to a full boil. Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Put in refrigerator and cool. Put in 1-quart strawberries that have been cleaned.
Frozen berries may be used, but reduce water to be added.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix coconut and milk together well by hand.
Form into 1/2-inch to 1-inch balls.
Place onto wax paper.
Freeze overnight.
Melt 1/2 package of chocolate and dip balls into chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Let stand approximately 30 minutes.
Serve.
(Can place toothpick into balls before freezing; makes balls easier to dip into chocolate.)

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine egg and 1/4 cup of the soup.
Stir in uncooked rice, onion, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 20 small balls; place in a 10-inch skillet.
Mix remaining soup with Worcestershire and 1/2 cup water; pour over meatballs.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes; stir often.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: chestnut cake(dort kastanovy)
directions: To prepare chestnuts, wash them and make incisions on the rounded sides.
Roast in a preheated 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Peel.
Cook in milk for about 30 minutes.
Rub through a strainer while hot, adding to puree whatever liquid has not been absorbed in cooking process, but reserve 1/4 cup of chestnuts for decorating cake.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water (just enough to cover) until tender.
Add corn.
Heat to simmering stage, add salt and pepper to taste and some margarine.
Then add milk, about a cup per person. Don't boil, but serve hot.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: gumbo
directions: Make roux (light or dark as desired) with small amount of grease, flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Set aside.
Saute bell pepper, onion and sausage in large stainless pot.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, bay leaves, file and cayenne pepper.
Add water until desired quantity of gumbo is reached.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium for 2 hours.
Add shrimp.
Cook on medium heat until shrimp is done.
Serve over bed of rice.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix flour, butter and cream cheese by hand until evenly mixed until mixture is similar to modeling clay.
Roll out on a cloth, well coated with powdered sugar, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut dough in strips 1-inch wide, 2-inches long.
Roll around nuts, dates and cherries and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
They do not get brown, unless ruined.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot from oven.
Chill thoroughly and enjoy.

title: recipe for a martin family reunion(dedicated to all of the tom & liza martin descendants)
directions: Start with 2 good people.
Strain off 10 children.
Mix these 10 children with the opposite sex.
After this mixture, you end up with approximately 49 of the grandest grandchildren.
After these 49 grandchildren, you need a desire for them to care for each other and be proud of who they are.
This is like a starter cake...you need something to keep the seedlings interested year after year.
Throw in a 3 day weekend filled with fun, games and visiting.
Mix with lots and lots of love.
You end up with a Martin Family Reunion.
(May not be fat free, but it is good for your heart and soul!!!)
This is considered an appetizer...it curbs your appetite a little, but it makes you hungrier for more!

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and persimmon pulp.
Blend into dry ingredients and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad supreme
directions: Choose fruit and jello flavors to match, e.g., orange jello with mandarin oranges, mixed fruit jello with fruit cocktail, lime jello with pears or pineapple.
Can be any combination you like. Drain fruit well.
Combine Cool Whip, cottage cheese and fruit in a bowl.
Add dry jello powder and mix well.
Refrigerate until set.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Brown meat; drain and set aside.
Combine next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Place in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sanders buttercream frosting
directions: Boil 1 cup of whole milk twice (two times and let cool completely between the two times).
This is the secret. Do not rush this or the frosting won't whip together.
Beat the egg whites, dry, by themselves.
Then gradually add the sugar and beat hard.
Add real butter at room temperature and beat again.
Add cooled milk slowly.
Add vanilla and keep beating until mixture comes together into a creamy mixture that holds peaks.

title: english pea salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients and refrigerate overnight in a covered bowl.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa together 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture, along with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and cake coloring.
Fold in vinegar and soda (mixed in a cup until smooth).
Bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread on center of platter.
Surround with Ritz crackers for dipping.
Top shrimp dip with cocktail sauce.

title: hawaiian carrot cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in
one	bowl with wooden spoon. Pour into
greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake at 350° about 55 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add jar of spaghetti sauce and Italian seasoning. Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes. In large bowl, mix all cheeses and parsley flakes. Spray 11 x 14 baking dish with Pam. Put 1 cup of sauce in bottom of baking dish. Then add layer of noodles followed by layer of sauce on each of the noodles, then layer of cheese. Repeat layers: noodles, sauce and cheese until you have used all ingredients, finishing with layer of cheese. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Mix and make lattice design on top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: catfish cabin slaw
directions: Grate cabbage; sprinkle with sugar.
Let set for 1 hour. Grate carrots.
Dice onion.
Drain juice off cabbage; mix with carrot and onion mixture.
Add sweet salad cubes and salad dressing.
Chill.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in layer cake pans. Cool completely.
Combine milk and flour and cook until thick; allow to cool.
In bowl, mix sugar, salt, Crisco, oleo and vanilla.
Using mixer, beat good, adding flour and milk mixture a little at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Cut the layers of cake in two and ice between layers.
You'll have 4 layers when you are finished, but you have plenty of icing to apply a thick layer. Keep refrigerated.
It really tastes like Twinkies.

title: hot mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown meats; drain well.
Place in bottom of crock-pot.
In the meantime, melt Velveeta cheese with milk over very low heat. Add melted cheese and remaining ingredients to crock-pot; mix well.
Ole!

title: jimmie's hawaiian gloop!
directions: Mix all ingredients in 6-quart ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Peel and cut up apples and oranges.
Grind the cranberries. Take 2 cups of boiling hot water and mix in jello.
Let cool.
Then mix sugar in cranberries, apples, oranges, nuts and the drained crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Let set up overnight.
Keeps well in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain. Brown ground
beef,
onion
and pepper.
Drain well. Add salt, chili powder, red pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cook on low for 15 to 20
minutes. Add tomato sauce or juice and then add spaghetti. Simmer several minutes. Stir often.

title: preserves(apple, citron, pear or peach)
directions: Mix the fruit and sugar well; let stand overnight.
Cook until fruit is transparent and juice drips 2 drops at a time from spoon. Pour into jars and seal.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Blend together well and chill.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef, sugar and seasonings. Stir in sauces and noodles. Put layer of mixture in pan then layer of cheese and another layer of mix. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mama's good pickles
directions: Drain dills.
Bring sugar, spices and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over dills.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain all other ingredients.
Do not drain off excess liquids from corn and beans.
Add all liquids. Simmer and serve.
Great in crock-pot.

title: round steak and gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into deep baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 325°
for 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend eggs and bananas.
Add combined ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Spread Crunchy Topping over warm cake.
Broil until bubbly and golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: *Brown sugar may be substituted for granulated sugar.

title: heath dessert
directions: Mix and pat crumbs and butter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix ice cream, pudding and milk.
Beat together until smooth.
Pour onto cooled crust.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle on top.

title: bacon water chestnuts(preparation time: 20 minutes; cooking time: 45 minutes)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon in large skillet on medium heat until almost cooked, but still a bit limp.
Drain.

title: tina
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Put first 6 ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Mix with electric mixer until there is a smooth texture.
Knead in the 8 cups of white flour to a soft, workable dough.
Let rise in a warm area until doubled in size.

title: citrus fluff
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and stir to dissolve.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in whipped topping and beaten egg whites.
Chill.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: rum sauce(for bread pudding, cake, ice cream)
directions: Mix sugar and cream in pan.
Heat over medium heat.
Mix in the butter.
Stir in the rum.
